LONG-TERM LEASE WITH INCREASES: Panera Bread has 14 years remaining on their NNN lease with three (3), 5-year renewal options. Panera Bread‚Äôs lease features a 10% rent increase every 5 years and at the start of each option period, and Metro Mattress‚Äôs lease also features for attractive rent increases every 5 years throughout their base term and renewal options providing the investor with an attractive increase in revenue and hedge against inflation.

MINIMAL MANAGEMENT RESPONSIBILITIES: Both Panera Bread‚Äôs and Metro Mattress‚Äôs leases are NNN. Both tenants reimburse their pro-rata share of operating expenses (real estate taxes, insurance, and common area maintenance) as well as all repairs and maintenance to the buildings, making it an attractive investment for the passive real estate investor.

Metro Mattress has been in business for more than 45 years, primarily serving New York State. They have recently expanded into Connecticut, Massachusetts, Rhode Island and New Hampshire. The growing company has more than 60 locations.

PRIME RETAIL LOCATION: 769 Bridgeport Avenue is extremely well located at the center of a busy retail, medical and corporate office corridor situated along Bridgeport Avenue between Route 8 and the Trapp Falls Reservoir in Fairfield County. The area is home to more than 5,000,000 square feet of corporate office and flex space, and numerous shopping centers with national retailers and restaurants, all of which drive traffic to the area. Shelton offers a captive employment market that provides a built-in customer base for the tenants in Fountain Square. The destination trade area serves the surrounding towns of Seymour, Ansonia, Derby, Monroe, and Trumbull, as well as travelers on CT Route 8, a primary commuter highway which sees more than 68,500 vehicles per day.

CORPORATE OFFICE CORRIDOR: Notable corporate tenants include Prudential Financial, CDW, United Healthcare, Robert Half, Barnum Financial Group, Sectra North America, Tetley USA, Baldwin Technology, Black & Decker, BIC Corporation, Playtex, Perkin Elmer and Pitney Bowes.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: Over 16,200 vehicles pass the Property every day along Bridgeport Avenue. An additional 68,500 vehicles pass the trade area daily on CT Route 8.

DEMOGRAPHICS: Approximately 35,000 people live within 3-miles of the Property with an average household income of $152,658. A Variety of Value Enhancement Opportunities ‚Äì The Offering‚Äôs Net Operating Income is based on in-place projections at 68% occupancy.‚Äã The vacancy is a second-story 3,000 square-foot office suite in cold dark shell condition.‚Äã The high ceiling space has the potential for a roof deck.‚Äã Investors may seek to occupy this space as a user, create a separate condominium and sell off the unit, or lease it to stabilize the investment.‚Äã ¬†

Investors will also find upside in the parking space revenues which are approximately 13% of the property‚Äôs overall gross revenues across a total of 30 leasable spaces.‚Äã This is a high-demand parking area.‚Äã For multiple decades this lot has served as leased parking to users of this site and surrounding businesses.‚Äã With significant development taking place around it, much of the surface parking has been developed vertically including a surface lot immediately across Aliceanna Street.‚Äã Presently, there are nine unleased spaces which could increase the annual income by $16,200.‚Äã Additionally, an investor can continue to raise overall rent rates beyond the current market of $150 per month which has been done recently by ownership.‚Äã

Additional Parking Upside - The recent departures of two food-trucks provides upside potential as they occupied a total of three spaces.‚Äã REEF Services was paying $2,000 per month, while a second food truck was paying $300 per month.‚Äã The REEF location has all utilities installed.‚Äã The estimated $16,200 potential from increased parking revenues assumes no new food-trucks are added to the lot.‚Äã

Lastly, Ownership is entering into an agreement with S&P+ Parking for ticketing and evening parking via electronic gating and periodic patrol of the lot.‚Äã The revenues from this agreement have not been modeled into projections, but will be shared 50/50 with S&P+ and new ownership over the present base of revenues.‚Äã It is estimated that an owner may benefit from an additional $20,888 per year once this agreement is operational.‚Äã

Occupancy and WALT ‚Äì With average in place rents of approximately $15.25 psf (in-line tenants) and $9.75 psf (anchor tenants), the center is positioned as the low cost provider in the trade area and therefore provides a significant value add opportunity to increase rents. All the anchor stores (51,219 sf, 54% of total occupancy) have been tenants at the center for approximately 15 years or greater. This has helped increase foot-traffic and maintain stable occupancy over time. The property boasts 98% occupancy with 2.5 years of WALT remaining as of 8/1/2023. This provides stable and consistent yield with the ability to strategically implement new tenancy and increase net operating income over time.

Dynamic Retail Location ‚Äì The center is located just 17 minutes from downtown Salt Lake City and 16 minutes from Salt Lake City International Airport, which is completing its $5.1B expansion and renovation. This asset is situated on Redwood Road which is a main traffic boulevard running north and south and features seamless connectivity to both I-15 and I-215. There are two grocers within a one-block radius, Smith‚Äôs Foods and Lucky Stores, both of which generate considerable traffic for the trade area.

Strong Area Demographics ‚Äì This asset is strategically positioned within 5 miles of 139,557 households with a total population of 405,243 residents that feature strong average household incomes of $99,608. Within a one-mile radius there are 5,866 households with average household incomes of $106,007. Redwood Road and 7000 South serve as the main transportation corridors for these residents with 42,400 vehicles per day on Redwood Road and 26,920 vehicles per day on 7000 South.

Retail Market Resilience ‚Äì Even in the face of economic challenges, the American consumer has shown resilience. In July 2023, retail sales increased by 0.7% compared to June, and they saw a 3.2% rise from July 2022. On the commercial real estate side, the national retail vacancy rate tightened to 5.4% in Q2 2023. The Salt Lake City retail market‚Äôs vacancy stands at 3.9%, among the nation lowest. Meanwhile, asking rents experienced a growth of 4.7% over the past year, reaching $23.47 per square foot.

marketingDescription:
Welcome to Gordon Street Plaza: Alvin's Charming Neighborhood Shopping Center

Location: Gordon Street, Alvin, TX

Nestled on the bustling Gordon Street that runs through the heart of Alvin, Texas, Gordon Street Plaza is a beloved neighborhood shopping center that has been a cornerstone of the community since 1981.‚Äã This 5,550 square foot commercial gem is the perfect blend of convenience, history, and modern amenities.‚Äã

Community Hub:

Gordon Street Plaza isn't just a shopping center; it's the beating heart of the Alvin community.‚Äã With three dedicated entrances, it seamlessly connects the town's residents with their favorite local businesses.‚Äã This well-designed layout offers convenience and accessibility, making it a go-to destination for both regular patrons and newcomers.‚Äã

Long-Standing Tenants:

Two of the three spaces in Gordon Street Plaza have been occupied by cherished local businesses for many years.‚Äã These tenants have not only become integral parts of the community but also add to the center's warm and welcoming atmosphere.‚Äã The longstanding presence of these businesses is a testament to the strong sense of community and loyalty that defines Alvin.‚Äã

Modern Comfort and Convenience:

Despite its historic roots, Gordon Street Plaza is equipped with all the modern conveniences you'd expect from a contemporary shopping center.‚Äã The spacious 5,550 square feet of retail space provides ample room for businesses to thrive, while the concrete parking lot ensures hassle-free parking for visitors.‚Äã

Retail Variety:

Gordon Street Plaza is home to a diverse range of businesses, catering to the needs and tastes of Alvin's residents.‚Äã From local boutiques to essential services, you'll find a variety of options within its walls, making it a one-stop destination for shopping, dining, and more.‚Äã

A Piece of Alvin's History:

Built in 1981, Gordon Street Plaza is not just a shopping center; it's a piece of Alvin's history.‚Äã Its timeless design and enduring presence on Gordon Street make it a beloved landmark for both residents and visitors.‚Äã

Join Our Community:

Gordon Street Plaza welcomes new businesses to join our vibrant community and become part of Alvin's rich tapestry.‚Äã With dedicated entrances, loyal patrons, and a prime location on the main street, your business can thrive in this welcoming environment.‚Äã

Gordon Street Plaza: Where history meets modern convenience, and community is at the core.‚Äã Come and experience the charm of Alvin's beloved neighborhood shopping center.‚Äã

investmentHighlights:
PROPERTY ZONING: The Property is zoned B-2: General Business District. The B-2: General Business District is intended to apply to certain arterial streets where business establishments may be located to serve large sections of the city and adjacent areas. Such businesses need a conspicuous and accessible location convenient for motorists. Uses are particularly oriented toward meeting the full service needs of city residents. This is one of the most versatile zoning designations and allows for a variety of uses including but not limited to: financial institutions, office space, medical and dental office space, service establishments, retail establishments, and restaurants (carry-out, full-service, sit down, quick-serve).

VALUE ADD OPPORTUNITY: The 5,125 square foot building is situated on a 0.60- acre corner lot along Prospect Road. The Property benefits from excellent visibility and frontage along two roads and ample on-site parking. The versatile Property is currently configured for five retail suites, but they can be easily combined to accommodate larger spaces, allowing an owner to draw from a larger pool of prospective tenants. The Property is also ideal for an owner-user taking advantage of the excellent location of the underlying real estate.

STRATEGIC LOCATION: The Property is well located on Prospect Road and is just seconds from N Andrews Avenue (SR 811A), Powerline Road (SR 845) and Commercial Boulevard (SR 870), the area‚Äôs primary east-west commercial and commuter corridor. 480-490 Prospect Road is 1-mile from Interstate 95, 2-miles from Federal Highway (US Route 1), 4-miles from the Florida Turnpike, and 4.5-miles from downtown Fort Lauderdale. The Property also boasts two municipal bus stops 0.3-miles away, one on Powerline Road and one on N Andrews Avenue, and is 1.8-miles from the Cypress Creek Tri-Rail Station and is 8-miles from the Fort Lauderdale-Hollywood International Airport.

AREA RETAILERS: Additional retailers in the area include Home Depot, Lowe‚Äôs, Publix, Aldi, Ross, Five Below, Crunch Fitness, Walgreens, Dollar Tree, O‚ÄôReilly Auto Parts, AutoZone, Starbucks, Chipotle, McDonald‚Äôs, Burger King, Wendy‚Äôs, Denny‚Äôs, Popeyes, Arby‚Äôs, Smoothie King, Miami Grill, Dunkin‚Äô, 7-Eleven, and Wawa.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: More than 22,000 vehicles pass the Property along Prospect Road. An additional 150,700+ vehicles pass near the Property daily along Interstate 95.

DEMOGRAPHICS: There are approximately 138,300 people within a three-mile radius of the property with an average household income of $102,633. An impressive 410,000+ people within a 5-mile radius of the property with average household incomes of $99,720. The 5-mile area is also home to more than 287,200 employees.

marketingDescription: Marcus & Millichap‚Äôs Brown Retail Group has been selected to exclusively market for sale 192nd Plaza, a newly developed retail center located in rapidly growing Camas, WA (Portland/Vancouver MSA).‚Äã The Property is currently 92.4% occupied with pending LOIs on two vacant suites, which the Seller will guarantee for two years post-closing.‚Äã Nearly 80% of the GLA has occupied the Property for more than 6 years.‚Äã The Seller's current loan, fixed at a 5.00% interest rate until March, 2026 and amortized over 30 years, is assumable and features a balance of roughly $6,300,000 (contact listing agent for additional details).‚Äã Regus occupies approximately 42% of the GLA at the Property and is only paying $6.60/SF NNN in rent, with market rents achievable in the $20/SF - $22/SF NNN range, providing an investor with significant upside in increasing rents for this space to market.‚Äã All of the tenants at the Property currently operate on NNN leases allowing for reimbursement of nearly all expenses and providing a hedge against rising operating expenses.‚Äã The Property features a total of eleven tenants with varying lease expiration dates, ensuring long-term occupancy levels.‚Äã The Property was built in 2010, features high-quality finishes and has been maintained in great condition.‚Äã The Property benefits from a population of over 165,000 residents within a 5-mile radius, with average household incomes exceeding $105,000.‚Äã Within a 5-mile radius, the population has grown nearly 20% since 2010 and is projected to increase by another 4.6% in the next 5 years.‚Äã Within a 1-mile radius, the population has grown by more than 36% since 2010.‚Äã Camas, WA submarket rents have increased a cumulative 9.5% over the past three years, per CoStar.‚Äã With only 5.0% retail footprint growth in the past decade and zero square feet of new retail space currently under construction, the development lull creates a high barrier to entry and demand for space remains high.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
FULLY LEASED RETAIL CENTER WITH STRONG HISTORICAL OCCUPANCY

The Property is currently 92.4% occupied with pending LOIs on two vacant suites, which the Seller will guarantee for two years post-closing. Nearly 80% of the GLA has occupied the Property for more than 6 years.

ATTRACTIVE ASSUMABLE FINANCING AVAILABLE

The Seller's current loan, fixed at a 5.00% interest rate until March, 2026 and amortized over 30 years, is assumable and features a balance of roughly $6,300,000. Contact listing agent for additional details.

BELOW MARKET RENT IN UPSTAIRS REGUS SUITE

Regus occupies approximately 42% of the GLA at the Property and is only paying $6.60/SF NNN in rent, with market rents achievable in the $20/SF - $22/SF NNN range, providing an Investor with significant upside in increasing rents for this space to market.

ATTRACTIVE NNN LEASE STRUCTURE

All of the tenants at the Property currently operate on NNN leases allowing for reimbursement of nearly all expenses and providing a hedge against rising operating expenses.

STAGGERED LEASE EXPIRATION DATES

The Property features a total of eleven tenants with varying lease expiration dates, ensuring long-term occupancy levels. In addition, multiple tenants at the Property have recently expressed interest in extending their lease terms.

HIGH-QUALITY 2010 CONSTRUCTION

The Property was built in 2010, features high-quality finishes and has been maintained in great condition.

STRONG, INCREASING CUSTOMER VISITS

The Property has seen an increase in customer visits by over 20% year-over-year, with over 312,000 visits in the last twelve months, per Placer.ai.

AFFLUENT, HIGH POPULATION GROWTH SUB-MARKET

The Property benefits from a population of over 165,000 residents within a 5-mile radius, with average household incomes exceeding $105,000, well above the national average. Within a 5-mile radius, the population has grown nearly 20% since 2010 and is projected to increase by another 4.6% in the next 5 years. Within a 1-mile radius, the population has grown by more than 36% since 2010.

STRONG RENT GROWTH (9.5%) AND HIGH BARRIER TO ENTRY MARKET

Camas/Washougal Submarket rents have increased a cumulative 9.5% over the past three years, per CoStar. With only 5.0% retail footprint growth in the past decade and zero square feet of new retail space currently under construction, the development lull creates a high barrier to entry and demand for space remains high.

STRATEGIC LOCATION SURROUNDED BY RESIDENTIAL DEVELOPMENT

The Property benefits from being surrounded by residential neighborhoods and apartments, including Westridge Lofts (100 units) and Grandview Place (154 units) directly adjacent to the Property, 192nd West Lofts (169 units) across the street, and Kielo at Grass Valley (276 units) within a quarter mile. The Property also provides services to the employees from the surrounding business campuses, including Fisher Investment‚Äôs headquarters and the Vancouver Innovation Center, a 179-acre master-planned campus catering to the high-tech, bio-tech, and light industrial industries.

EXCELLENT RETAIL LOCATION WITH STRONG VISIBILITY TO OVER 26,000 VPD

Located on a signalized, hard-corner with excellent visibility and exposure to over 26,000 VPD on SE 192nd Ave and SE 20th St. with multiple points of ingress and egress.

DIVERSE, SERVICE, AND DAILY NEEDS ORIENTED TENANT MIX

The Property is occupied with a mix of retail, medical, and professional service tenants offering a stable and diversified income stream.

INCOME TAX FREE STATE

Washington State is an income tax free state.

description: Core Strip Center in Downtown Riverside
marketingDescription: Progressive Real Estate Partners is pleased to present the opportunity to acquire the Shops at University Square‚Äî a 100% occupied commercial strip center leased to 6 high performing and diverse service tenants.‚Äã The property is situated in Downtown Riverside, which is currently undergoing a renaissance with an estimated $330 million of recently completed and ongoing retail, hotel, and public works projects driving significant traffic to the property.‚Äã The property features fully NNN leases with embedded 3% annual increases, a diverse income stream with no individual tenant accounting for more than 24% of the center‚Äôs income, and ideal space sizes ranging from 750 SF to 1,750 SF (larger tenant pool leading to lower vacancy risk).‚Äã The entire shopping center, including the subject property, was recently remodeled with a new fa√ßade.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
HIGH TRAFFIC STRIP CENTER - STRONG INVESTMENT FUNDAMENTALS

100% Leased to 6 E-Commerce Resistant Tenants ‚Äì The asset features a robust mix of internet resilient tenants whose uses cannot be easily duplicated online. Examples include RAD Coffee, Miss Donuts & Bagel, and Mariscos Taco Shop.

Fully NNN Leases ‚Äì All of the center‚Äôs tenants are on industry standard AIR NNN leases with no caps on property taxes, insurance, or CAM.

Diverse Tenant Mix ‚Äì Unlike a single tenant asset where all the asset‚Äôs income is tied to one lease, the subject property‚Äôs income is spread across 6 tenants with no individual tenant accounting for more than 24% of the center‚Äôs income.

Strong Income Growth ‚Äì All leases feature embedded 3% annual increases. The all-cash yield grows to an estimated 7.00% by 2027.

Limited Shop Space Competition ‚Äì Strip centers (with parking included) are limited in Downtown Riverside, resulting in less competition and lower vacancy rates.

Ideal Space Sizes Ranging from 750 SF to 1,750 SF ‚Äì Retail space under 2,500 SF tends to have the largest pool of replacement tenants, reducing vacancy risk and creating more upside potential as supply remains limited.

IRREPLACABLE DOWNTOWN RIVERSIDE LOCATION

Downtown Riverside Has Undergone a MAJOR Renaissance ‚Äì Recent projects include:

o Riverside Convention Center Remodel ($36 million)

o Brand New Riverside Main Library ($40 million)

o Riverside Culinary Academy ($28 million)

o Fox Theater Event Center ($32 million)

o Cheech Center/Riverside Art Museum ($13 million)

o Imperial Hardware Lofts (89 units)

o The Mark Luxury Apartments (162 units)

o CIRCA on Mission (13 luxury townhomes)

o Mission Heritage Plaza (72 units + retail)

o Riverside Food Lab (14 unique restaurants)

o Several new hotels recently completed and under construction (500+ new rooms)

Recent Facelift ‚Äì The entire shopping center, including the subject property, was recently remodeled with a new fa√ßade.

Adjacent by Established Community Grocery Store ‚Äì Maxi Foods has operated at the site for over 20 years. As the only grocery store located in Downtown Riverside, it has become vital to the area‚Äôs residents and draws significant traffic to the site.

RAD Coffee Recently Added ‚Äì With over 147,000 followers on Instagram and 4 locations across Southern California (and growing), RAD Coffee draws significant positive traffic to the center.

investmentHighlights:
North Oaks Plaza spans 268,893 square feet of rentable space, covering roughly 18.33 acres at the meeting point of Natural Bridge Road and Lucas-Hunt Road, positioned at the northeast corner.

‚Ä¢ The property features three one-story retail establishments and a three-story office structure. The total retail space available for lease is 268,893 SF, and the office space sums up to 25,023 SF.

‚Ä¢ Initially established in 1963, the center has seen significant renovations in the years 1994, 2007, and the latest in 2021. A vast parking area accommodates 4 parking slots for every 1,000 square feet of space, providing tenants a distinctive advantage in such a densely-packed area.

‚Ä¢ In 2021, the property benefited from an investment exceeding $3,000,000. This fund facilitated fresh renovations for GSA Social Security and Dedicated Senior Medical Center spaces, parking lot improvements, a new TPO roofing for the Save A Lot outlet, and a fresh paint coat for the plaza and the professional building.

‚Ä¢ The plaza is neighbored by standalone outlots, including Walgreens, McDonald‚Äôs, and Simmons Bank. These establishments enhance the overall traffic to the plaza and contribute to its vibrancy. As per data from Placer.AI, the McDonald‚Äôs outlet ranks in the top 30% of its locations nationwide, and the Walgreens is among the top 15%. However, these outlots aren't included in the plaza's offerings.

‚Ä¢ North Oaks Plaza boasts impressive visibility and multiple entrance and exit points, granting convenient access from any route. It has four entryways on Natural Bridge Road (11,295 VPD), one of which is a semi-signalized intersection. The plaza can also be reached through alternate paths, including a rear entrance on O‚ÄôNeil Avenue via Pasadena Boulevard. Additionally, a fully signalized junction lies close by, at the confluence of Natural Bridge Road and Lucas-Hunt Road, managing the dense traffic of these prominent routes.

Sherwood Village is an ideal investment that provides an investor with a reliable and stable retail property below replacement costs, providing a valuable entry point for an established retail opportunity while minimizing overall economic risk.‚Äã With the limited availability and low market vacancy, this Property is in a prime position for healthy cash flows for years to come in a market with little pressure from future construction.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
Advantageous Cost Basis: The ability to acquire the Property well below replacement costs provides investors with a valuable entry point for an established multi-tenant retail opportunity, minimizing overall economic risk.

Secure Income Stream: The Property provides an investor with significant stability based on contractual rent paid by an evenly distributed composition, preventing concentration on one tenant or use. Strong Development Fundamentals with Prime Retail Location: The Property‚Äôs well-designed layout and lack of outparcels increase visibility and accessibility in the heart of Odessa‚Äôs main retail corridor.

Broad E-Commerce Resistant Tenant Mix: Sherwood Village‚Äôs prime location has made it the top destination for retailers within the trade area, resulting in a diverse collection of national, regional, and local tenants that are e-commerce-resistant and synergistic, creating a dynamic mix.

Thriving Retail Market: As part of the redevelopment, an additional 17,000 square feet of retail was built in 2020 and quickly absorbed, articulating the depth of the Odessa retail market. Odessa enjoys a very low vacancy of 2.10%, resulting in a cumulative rental increase of 12.20% over the past three years that will continue to trend based on minimal new developments, ensuring existing tenant retention and future tenant appeal if space becomes available.

Signalized Intersection with Robust Traffic: Sherwood Village is located on a heavily trafficked signalized intersection of Dixie Boulevard and East 42nd Street, which serves as a primary neighborhood thoroughfare for residents of the mature trade area. The Property‚Äôs tenants benefit from a combined 40,000 cars daily at the intersection.

marketingDescription:
Lee & Associates is pleased to present for sale the Fee Simple interest in ‚ÄúThe Shoppes at Meadowview‚Äù.‚Äã The subject property consists of a 15.14 acre site improved with 133,157 SF of retail space.‚Äã The property is currently 66.7% occupied, creating the opportunity to add value through the lease up of the vacancy.‚Äã The subject property is one of the largest and most diverse retail properties in Kankakee, IL less than 60 miles from downtown Chicago.‚Äã Meadowview has a diverse and unique merchandise mix focused on essential needs based tenants.‚Äã With a focus on fitness, discount retail and food and beverage, Meadowview has the ideal co-tenancy to attract best of class tenants during the stabilization and lease up process.‚Äã Meadowview will trade far below replacement cost providing a low basis to a new investor looking to achieve an above market yield during the hold / repositioning period and will further recognizing a significant return on equity at exit.‚Äã

The Shoppes at Meadowview has attractive in place financing that can be assumed.‚Äã The loan originated in 2021 with an original funding of $4,450,000 and benefits from an attractive below market 4% rate through 11/18/2026 then has a reset to 325 bps over the five-year treasury.‚Äã The debt amortizes on a 25-year schedule.‚Äã The term is 10 years and has a maturity date of 11/17/2023.‚Äã An investor has the ability to assume the in-place debt benefiting from the below market 4% rate with a runway of nearly 3 years to affect the reposition in advance of the reset and look to exit the deal or originate new permanent financing.‚Äã

The Shoppes at Meadowview is a rare opportunity to acquire a retail asset with a true value add strategy less than 60 miles from Chicago.‚Äã With exceptional visibility, strong fundamentals and the ability to assume debt with a below market rate, the Shoppes at Meadowview is the preeminent add value retail opportunity in the greater Chicago area.‚Äã

investmentHighlights:
UNIQUE COASTAL LOCATION

Located two short blocks is Moonlight Beach, considered to be one of the finest beaches in southern California and the center of recreation and social life in Encinitas. This sand beach has numerous convenient facilities including volleyball courts, playground equipment, tennis courts, picnic facilities, restrooms and showers, lifeguards, fire pits and snack bar. From Moonlight Beach, you can walk along the beach for miles in either direction. World famous Swami‚Äôs Beach is just a short walk along the beach to the south. Swami‚Äôs Surf Beach, made famous by the Beach Boys in ‚ÄúSurfin‚Äô USA,‚Äù still draws the finest surfers in the world on a daily basis.

WALKABLE LOCATION

The Lofts at Moonlight Beach is just a short walk from the Downtown 101 shopping district, which features historic architecture, quaint shops, sidewalk caf√©s, and restaurants. The site is also within walking distance to the Encinitas Coaster station, providing commuter train service between Oceanside and downtown San Diego. The Coaster line connects to Amtrak‚Äôs Pacific Surfliner Trains at the Solana Beach station. Other walkable locations include the public library offering a host of programs that are well-attended by the community and meet a variety of interests.

DEBT FREE

The site allows the investor the ability to obtain new financing at attractive terms, enhancing leveraged cash on cash returns.

E-COMMERCE RESISTANT

Retail and professional services represented at the site includes health and beauty, medical services, pet grooming and restaurant uses. These categories have proven to be difficult to replicate online and ensure the centers long term vitality.

OFF STREET PARKING

The center has 21 dedicated spaces in the underground garage for the commercial tenants and customers. There are also parallel public parking spaces along the frontage on Encinitas blvd. and along A Street to the north of the property.

HIGH TRAFFIC

You can‚Äôt beat this location if you are a restaurant or retailer looking for a prime coastal San Diego presence. With an established growing community, the site caters heavily to residents while benefiting from a solid daytime and visitor population.

marketingDescription:
CBRE is pleased to present, as the exclusive advisor, the opportunity to acquire King City Square, a Kroger-anchored neighborhood grocery center in Mount Vernon, Illinois, located 75 miles east of downtown St.‚Äã Louis.‚Äã

King City Square is anchored by a dominant Kroger store with a fuel center (Fuel Center is NAP) that did over $42 million in 2022 sales, a 1.5% increase over 2021, and 24% over pre-COVID 2019.‚Äã King City Square has a host of complimentary retailers to Kroger in fashion and beauty, apparel, pet supplies, and food and beverage.‚Äã The shopping center is 93.2% occupied and features 6,415 square feet of vacant space available for lease-up.‚Äã

With its strategic location along Broadway Street, the main retail thoroughfare in Mount Vernon, King City Square benefits from its proximity to national retailers such as Dunham‚Äôs Sports, Big Lots, Ross Dress for Less, Walmart Supercenter, Kohl‚Äôs, Aldi, and Lowe‚Äôs.‚Äã In addition, King City Square is a half mile east of Interstate 57 and Interstate 64, providing strong regional access to the shopping center.‚Äã

King City Square presents a tremendous opportunity for a future owner to acquire a top-performing Kroger anchored center with a strong value-add opportunity through the lease-up of the vacant suites.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
• ‚Äã

    Anchored by Dominant Kroger Grocer: Kroger at King City Square is the dominant grocer in the market, with January 2023 T-12 sales of almost $43 million. Sales increased by 24% over pre-COVID 2019 figures. Kroger ranks in the top 25% of Kroger stores in Illinois in foot traffic rankings according to the Placer.ai.

  • ‚Äã

    Lack of Grocery Competition: There is a true lack of grocery competition in the market, with only Walmart and Aldi providing alternative options for grocery shopping. This is the only Kroger location within a 25-mile radius, and there are no full-service grocers within this same radius.

  • ‚Äã

    Value-Add Opportunity: There are two suites totaling 6,415 square feet available for lease-up. If these suites are leased at market rental rates, a future owner can increase in place NOI by approximately 17%.

  • ‚Äã

    Recent Leasing Momentum: King City Square has experienced strong leasing momentum with the recent renewals from VIP Nails, and Asian Buffet, and the new LOI with 101 Tobacco Shop. The leasing momentum demonstrates the desirability of King City Square and the tenants‚Äô long-term commitment to the property.

  • ‚Äã

    Complimentary Retailers: King City Square features a complimentary tenant mix with retail categories in fashion and beauty, apparel, pet supplies, and food and beverage. There are 1.3 million annual visits to the shopping center, according to Placer.ai, of which the shops generate 455,000 visits or 35% of the annual traffic.

  • ‚Äã

    Strategic Location Along Broadway Street Retail Corridor: King City Square is located along Broadway Street, the main retail corridor in Mount Vernon, Illinois. Adjacent to the shopping center is Times Square Mall, home to national retailers like Dunham‚Äôs Sports, Big Lots, Bath & Body Works, and Ross Dress for Less. Other prominent national retailers along the corridor include Walmart Supercenter, Kohls, Aldi, and Lowe‚Äôs.

  • ‚Äã

    Regional Access and High Traffic Counts: King City Square is located on Broadway and 42nd Streets with over 27,000 VPD. Broadway Street is the main east-west retail thoroughfare. A half mile east is Interstate 57, which runs north to Chicago, and Interstate 64, which connects St. Louis and Louisville. As a result of this strong regional location, there are over 1,100 hotel rooms in the immediate area.

marketingDescription:
SRS Investment Properties Group, as exclusive broker, is pleased to present the opportunity to acquire Candies Creek ‚Äì a 30,196¬± SF neighborhood center, anchored by a brand new Dollar Tree and located in Cleveland, TN.‚Äã

Anchored by Dollar Tree with a 10-Year Lease

Candies Creek is anchored by a brand-new Dollar Tree with term through 2034.‚Äã Occupying 15,674¬± SF, Dollar Tree provides an incoming buyer with a strong, expanding national anchor on which to build in executing the lease-up of the remaining 3,750¬± SF of available space.‚Äã

¬†

Major Road Expansion: TN-60

Well-positioned at the signalized intersection of Paul Huff Pkwy and TN-60 ‚Äì two of Cleveland‚Äôs primary traffic thoroughfares - Candies Creek accesses 31,965 VPD in front of the Property.‚Äã Bolstering consumer accessibility, TN-60 is currently undergoing a $54M project to expand the road from two to five lanes, including a new Candies Creek bridge, a dedicated center turn lane, expanded shoulders and sidewalks, and upgraded street lighting.‚Äã Significant synergistic retail development along the expansion and adjacent to the Property includes Fast Pace Health Urgent Care, Creekside Veterinary Clinic, and McDonald‚Äôs, along with existing outparcels ‚Äì Walgreen‚Äôs and O‚ÄôReilly‚Äôs.‚Äã

¬†

Cleveland, TN¬†

Candies Creek Shopping Center is located in Cleveland, TN ‚Äì the county seat and largest city within Bradley County.‚Äã A principal component of the Chattanooga-Cleveland-Dalton, TN-GA CSA, Cleveland lies roughly 30 miles northeast of Downtown Chattanooga and 80 miles southwest of Knoxville.‚Äã Home to the Cherokee National Forest as well as the Ocoee and Hiwasee Rivers, the area boasts excellent whitewater rafting which draws visitors to the area almost year-round for outdoor recreation.‚Äã With 13 Fortune 500 manufacturing facilities, Cleveland boasts the fifth-largest industrial economy in Tennessee.‚Äã Major companies include Whirlpool, Duracell, Amazon, Coca-Cola, International Paper, Rock-Tenn, Rubbermaid and more.‚Äã Cleveland also serves as the corporate headquarters for Life Care Centers of America: the largest privately held nursing facility company in the United States.‚Äã

marketingDescription: Marcus & Millichap's Brown Retail Group has been selected to exclusively market for sale a trophy Starbucks anchored center located in rapidly growing Wenatchee, WA.‚Äã The Property includes the only drive-thru Starbucks in all of Wenatchee and East Wenatchee and is located at the main entrance to Wenatchee's high barrier-to-entry retail trade area.‚Äã The Property is 100% occupied with a mix of four total tenants including Starbucks (since 2005), FedEx (since 2006), Abundant Life Chiropractic (since 2013), and Love Sushi (since 2021).‚Äã The Property benefits from strong visibility to over 35,000 VPD and large pylon signage.‚Äã To go along with the property's highly desirable location, the Wenatchee market currently features a 1.1% retail vacancy rate, per CoStar.‚Äã The Subject property is located near two major national tenants, Wal-Mart and Home Depot, that provide consistent traffic draw to the immediate area.‚Äã The roof was replaced in 2018 and features a 60ml TPO membrane.‚Äã All Tenants at the center operate on NNN leases, minimizing Landlord management/repair responsibility.‚Äã The city has grown by over 10% within the past decade and has a limited amount of available land left to develop making the asset a highly stable retail center with strong appreciation potential.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
TROPHY STARBUCKS ANCHORED CENTER

The Property includes the only drive-thru Starbucks in all of Wenatchee and East Wenatchee and is located at the main entrance to Wenatchee's high barrier to entry retail trade area. Starbucks has occupied the property since 2005, when the property was built.

100% OCCUPIED WITH DIVERSE TENANT MIX

The Property is 100% occupied with a mix of four total tenants including Starbucks (since 2005), FedEx (since 2006), Abundant Life Chiropractic (since 2013), and Love Sushi (since 2021).

HIGH BARRIER TO ENTRY MARKET WITH 1.1% VACANCY RATE AND 15% RENT GROWTH

Wenatchee MSA currently boasts a 1.1% retail vacancy rate and 15% rent growth over the past three years, per CoStar, making it one of the tightest retail markets in the state of Washington. With only 2.80% retail footprint growth in the past decade, zero square feet of new retail space delivered in the past 12 months, and zero square feet of retail space currently under construction, the development lull creates an incredibly high barrier to entry as demand for space remains high.

HIGH-VISIBILITY LOCATION WITH STRONG TRAFFIC COUNTS (35,000+ VPD)

The Property benefits from strong visibility to over 35,000 VPD and large pylon signage.

BRAND NEW ROOF

The roof was replaced in 2018 and features a 60 mil TPO membrane.

SHADOW ANCHORED BY LARGE NATIONAL TENANTS

The subject property is located near two major national tenants, Wal-Mart and Home Depot, that provide consistent traffic draw to the immediate area.

SCHEDULED RENT INCREASES AND STRONG NOI GROWTH

Each of the tenants at the Property have scheduled rent increases during the firm term and options periods providing for strong contractual NOI growth.

LOW MANAGEMENT CENTER WITH ALL NNN LEASES

All tenants at the center operate on NNN leases, minimizing Landlord management/repair responsibility.

AFFLUENT, HIGH POPULATION GROWTH MARKET

The Property benefits from a population of over 62,000 people within a 5-mile radius, with average household incomes exceeding $85,000. Within a 5-mile radius, the population has grown over 10% since 2010 and is projected to increase by another 3.0% in the next 5 years. Within a 1-mile radius, the population has grown by more than 15% since 2010.

INCOME TAX FREE STATE

Washington State is an Income Tax-Free state.

The brand-new 8,600+ square foot building is positioned along Main Street in Indianapolis.‚Äã Speedway has quickly grown into a popular destination for the local population and regional visitors alike.‚Äã The building lies in the shadow of the Indianapolis Motor Speedway, home of The Greatest Spectacle in Racing: the Indy 500.‚Äã During this event, Main Street will see more than a quarter of a million visitors.‚Äã¬† Main Street is home to several racing industry headquarters, Prax Air, Big Woods, Charlie Brown‚Äôs, and many other local favorites.‚Äã The delivery of several apartment buildings along main street will continue to increase the need for retail and office demand in the area.‚Äã

LEASE TERM: Big Lots signed a new 10-year lease in 2020 and they have 7+ years remaining on their corporate lease with three (3), 5-year renewal options.

ATTRACTIVE RENT INCREASES: The Big Lots lease calls for attractive $1.00 per square foot increases in rent increase every 5 years throughout the base term and at the start of each renewal option period providing the investor with an attractive increase in revenue and hedge against inflation.

STRONG CORPORATE TENANT: The Property features a corporate guarantee with Big Lots, one of the most sought-after discount retailers in the country. Big Lots, Inc. is a community retailer operating more than 1,400 Big Lots stores in 47 states, they are traded on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol BIG.

UPSIDE POTENTIAL: The Property features a vacant end-cap unit consisting of 4,055 square feet. The opportunity exists to significantly increase the revenue at the Property through the lease up of the vacant space. The center offers outstanding visibility, frontage, and parking and has a national anchor, further increasing the desirability of the space in the leasing market.

MINIMAL LANDLORD RESPONSIBILITIES: Big Lots has a net lease and reimburses their pro-rata share real estate taxes and insurance. They also pay a fixed Common Area Maintenance fee that increases by 3% annually. The current Common Area Maintenance fee is $72,565.56 ($2.02 per square foot) which exceeds the annual common area maintenance changes.

PRIME RETAIL LOCATION: The Property is well located along Main Street (MA Route 28) and benefits from outstanding visibility and frontage. The Property is 1-mile from MA Route 134, the area‚Äôs primary north south corridor which provides direct access to US Route 6 and the shores of the Cape Cod Bay. The Big Lots Center is part of the trade area centered along MA Route 28 near the border of Dennis and Harwich with numerous hotels and motels, businesses, national and local retailers, restaurants, and proximity to Cape Cod‚Äôs southern beaches and harbors, all of which draw significant traffic to the area.

ECONOMIC DRIVERS: Dennisport‚Äôs economy is closely tied to its status as a popular tourist destination on Cape Cod. Dennisport benefits from a diverse range of businesses and services that cater to both residents and the influx of seasonal tourists who flock to the area during the summer months. Tourism is the backbone of Dennisport's economy. The village's proximity to beautiful Nantucket Sound beaches, such as Sea View Beach, Glendon Road Beach, and Haigis Beach, makes it a sought-after destination for vacationers. A significant portion of the local economy relies on tourism-related businesses. Dennisport's Main Street is lined with charming boutiques, gift shops, and galleries that draw people to the area. These establishments cater to both tourists and local residents. The summer season is especially lucrative for these businesses, as vacationers explore the village and shop for souvenirs and unique items.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: On average more than 12,300 vehicles pass the Property daily along Main Street (MA Route 28). The traffic counts during the summer months (peak season) often double or triple.

DEMOGRAPHICS: Approximately 38,200 people live within 5-miles of the Property with an average household income of $105,970. More than 93,100 people live within 5-miles of the Property with an average household income of $116,361. Additionally, the population in the area swells to more than triple in the summer months as vacationers from the Greater Boston Area and throughout the northeast descend on Cape Cod.

Petco Plaza is situated in an exceptional location along the Route 114 corridor, at the well-trafficked, signalized intersection of Sylvan Street and Andover Street (Route 114).‚Äã The Property benefits from excellent visibility and frontage, as well as three points of access and ample parking.‚Äã Petco Plaza is down the street from the Northshore Mall, the dominant shopping center serving Boston‚Äôs northeastern suburbs, at the junction of Route 114 and Route 128.‚Äã The entire trade area features an extensive lineup of major national retailers and popular local businesses that make for the preeminent retail destination in Boston‚Äôs Northshore.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
STRONG ANCHOR TENANT: Petco has operated at this location since 1999 (24+ years) and occupies over 76% of the building area. Petco extended their lease by 10 years demonstrating their commitment to the site and the market. Their current lease has over 6 years remaining with two (2), 5-year renewal options. Petco is the second largest pet specialty retail chain in North America with over 1,500 stores and reported net sales of $5.97 billion for 2022.

OUTSTANDING LOCATION: The Property is exceptionally well-located at the well-trafficked, signalized intersection of Sylvan Street and Andover Street (Route 114), with outstanding visibility and frontage on both streets. The location is part of a major trade area between Route 128 and Interstate 95, featuring an extensive lineup of major national retailers and popular local businesses driving significant traffic to the area. The Northshore Mall is down the street from the Property at the junction of Route 114 and 128, and offers an upscale shopping atmosphere with a generous variety of more than 130 specialty stores.

SCHEDULED RENT INCREASES: The Petco lease features scheduled 10% rent increases at the start of each of their two (2), 5-year renewal options. The Bagel World lease features annual 2% rental increases throughout their 5+ year term and option period. Atha‚Äôs Roast Beef & Pizza features an 11% rent increase at the start of their renewal option, with annual increases during the option, providing a steady increase in income and an attractive hedge against inflation.

MINIMAL MANAGEMENT RESPONSIBILITIES: Petco, Bagel World, and Atha‚Äôs Roast Beef & Pizza reimburse for the majority of their pro-rata share of all real estate taxes, operating expenses, repairs and maintenance to the entire property, making it an attractive investment for the passive investor.

UPSIDE POTENTIAL: The Property offers potential upside through lease-up of a 1,345 square foot vacant suite.

RETAIL TRADE AREA: Additional retailers driving traffic to the trade area include Nordstrom, Life Time Fitness, Target, Market Basket, CVS, Trader Joe‚Äôs, Home Depot, Shaw‚Äôs, Chase Bank, Bank of America, Starbucks, McDonald‚Äôs, Wendy‚Äôs, Taco Bell, Dick‚Äôs Sporting Goods, Best Buy, Kohl‚Äôs, Michaels, TJ Maxx, Nordstrom Rack, Bed Bath & Beyond, Dunkin‚Äô, Burlington, At Home, Macy‚Äôs, AutoZone, Firestone, Advance Auto Parts, and many others.

STRONG DEMOGRAPHICS: Over 94,700 people live within a 3-mile radius of the Property with an average household income of $101,916, while 215,900+ people live within 5 miles of the Property with an average household income of $107,907.

EXCELLENT TRAFFIC COUNTS: An average traffic count of over 77,600 vehicles per day pass by the Property at the signalized intersection of Sylvan Street and Andover Street (Route 114).

Prime Net Lease is pleased to present the exciting opportunity to acquire a 10,790 SF 6 unit multi-tenant retail center, known as the Gaslite Square Plaza, located in Milan, IL.‚Äã The tenant mix consists of retail-oriented tenants that conveniently serve customers in the nearby community and surrounding areas.‚Äã Most of the tenants have been long term, reliable and who have continuously maintained their leases throughout the years, showing their strong commitment to the area and site itself.‚Äã The plaza is located on one of Milan's busiest intersections with nearly 17,000 vehicles per day.‚Äã This has attracted the plaza's newest tenant, Bill's Gaming Cafe, who spent nearly $100,000 on recent renovations.‚Äã The site shares a parking lot with Dollar General, while directly next door are both KFC and AutoZone and across the street are Hy-Vee and CVS.‚Äã Local and major national tenants closeby include Pizza Hut, McDonald's, Hardee's, Jimmy John's, Fazoli's, Target, Ross, Hobby Lobby, Dollar General, Walgreens and many others.‚Äã

The site has quick access to US Hwy 92, I-280, I-74 & The Quad City Airport.‚Äã Milan is home to the John Deere North American Parts Distribution Center, one of the largest warehouses in the world.‚Äã In June of 2022, only six miles away in Davenport, Iowa, Fair Oaks Foods announced plans to construct a state-of-the-art food production facility.‚Äã The $134 million investment includes a 150,000 square-foot facility in the Eastern Iowa Industrial Center and will create an estimated 247 new full-time jobs.‚Äã The company plans to start operations in early 2024.‚Äã Construction is anticipated to begin this summer on a 32-acre site near Interstate 80.‚Äã This development is expected to have an annual economic impact of $182 million, making it the largest business attraction project in the region‚Äôs history.‚Äã

Milan is a village in Rock Island County, Illinois.‚Äã The village is located near the Quad Cities of Illinois and Iowa.‚Äã The area consists of the cities of Davenport and Bettendorf in Iowa and Rock Island, Moline, and East Moline in Illinois, and their suburbs in northwest Illinois and southeast Iowa.‚Äã The Quad Cities is located at the confluence of the Rock and Mississippi rivers, approximately 140 miles (230 km) west of Chicago, and forms the largest metropolitan area along the Mississippi River between Minneapolis‚ÄìSaint Paul and the St.‚Äã Louis metropolitan area.‚Äã The Quad Cities Metropolitan Area consists of three counties: Scott County in Iowa, and Rock Island County and Henry County in Illinois.‚Äã The Quad City metro population is 382,268.‚Äã The Quad Cities Metropolitan Area is also considered part of the Great Lakes Megalopolis.‚Äã

marketingDescription:
Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to acquire the new construction two-tenant plaza located at 1549 White Mountain Highway in North Conway, New Hampshire (the ‚ÄúProperty‚Äù).‚Äã The build to suit, two-tenant plaza is improved with Chipotle and Aspen Dental and contains 6,197 square feet on a 1.61-acre parcel.‚Äã The Property was completed in 2021, Chipotle has 7+ years remaining on their lease with four (4), 5-Year renewal options.‚Äã Aspen Dental signed a new 10-year lease with three (3), 5-year renewal options.‚Äã Aspen Dental‚Äôs space is under construction, and the seller will escrow their rent from closing until their rent commencement date.‚Äã Both tenants‚Äô leases call for attractive rent increases every 5-years throughout their primary lease terms and at the start of their renewal options.‚Äã

The Property is situated in one of the best locations in North Conway to capture passing motorists on the heavily-travelled US Route 302/NH Route 16 commercial corridor (White Mountain Highway) which includes most of the area‚Äôs retail, dining, lodging and entertainment options.‚Äã The Property is also located adjacent to the entrance for Settler‚Äôs Green, a popular 75-store, 500,000 square foot shopping center which helps drive considerable traffic to the area.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
NEW CONSTRUCTION: The Build-to-Suit Property was completed in 2021. Chipotle has 7+ years remaining on their lease with four (4), 5-year renewal options. Aspen Dental signed a new 10-year lease with three (3), 5-year renewal options. Aspen Dental‚Äôs space is under construction. Chipotle benefits from a modern design with outdoor seating and a Chipotlane (drive-thru).

ATTRACTIVE RENT INCREASES: The Chipotle lease calls for a 10% rent increase every 5 years throughout the base term and at the start of each option period and the Aspen Dental lease calls for a 10% increase in year 6 and 8% increases at the start of each renewal option providing the investor with an attractive increase in revenue and hedge against inflation.

MINIMAL LANDLORD RESPONSIBILITIES: Both Chipotle and Aspen Dental have net leases with minimal Landlord responsibilities. The tenants reimburse their pro-rata share of all operating expenses, repairs, and maintenance of the property, making it an attractive investment for the passive real estate investor.

DYNAMIC CORPORATE TENANTS: The Property features a corporate guarantee with Chipotle, one of the most sought-after restaurant brands in the country. Total revenue for 2021 was $7.54 billion, an increase of 26.11% from 2020. Chipotle opened 215 new restaurants during 2021 bringing the total restaurant count at year-end to 2,966. Chipotle planned to open an additional 225-250 locations in 2022, 80% of which are expected to included a Chipotlane. The Aspen Dental network includes 900 offices, in 43 states, owned and operated by independent practice owners and dentists, who operate with clinical autonomy and share a commitment to creating access to care for those who need it most. These independent practice owners recorded more than five million patient visits in 2021, driven by a commitment to breaking down barriers to quality, affordable oral health care.

CHIPOTLANE: Digital sales remain a major bright spot for the chain, growing 202.5% year over year to $776.4 million. Digital orders now make up 48.8% of sales, with about half of those orders for delivery and the rest for order-ahead transactions, such as instore pickup and Chipotlane drive-thrus. The drive-thrus (Chipotlanes) are significant for the chain, generating about 10% more in sales than those locations without them.

PRIME RETAIL LOCATION: The Property is situated in one of the best locations in North Conway to capture passing motorists on the heavilytravelled US Route 302/NH Route 16 commercial corridor (White Mountain Highway) which includes most of the area‚Äôs retail, dining, lodging and entertainment options. The Property is also located adjacent to the entrance for Settler‚Äôs Green, a popular 75-store, 500,000 square foot shopping center which helps drive considerable traffic to the area.

RECESSION & E-COMMERCE RESISTANT TENANT: With an Aging babyboomer population, and strong area demographics, the need for brick and mortar medical and dental office buildings will continue to increase. This industry is unaffected by recessions and the need for personal interaction and specific medical aids can not be satisfied through e-commerce.

RETAIL TRADE AREA: Digital sales remain a major bright spot for the chain, growing 202.5% year over year to $776.4 million. Digital orders now make up 48.8% of sales, with about half of those orders for delivery and the rest for order-ahead transactions, such as in-store pickup and Chipotlane drive-thrus. The drive-thrus (Chipotlanes) are significant for the chain, generating about 10% more in sales than those locations without them.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: More than 16,800 vehicles pass the Property daily along White Mountain Highway (US Route 302/NH Route 16).

DEMOGRAPHICS: Approximately 10,500 people live within 5-miles of the Property with an average household income of $89,393. More than 20,300 people live within 10-miles of the Property with an average household income of $90,649.

marketingDescription:
Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to purchase the Heights Professional Medical Plaza, an investment property located at 11721- 11761 Southwest Highway in Palos Heights, Illinois (the ‚ÄúProperty‚Äù).‚Äã The Property is improved by a 61,638 square foot two-story building (both levels are at grade) that contains 37,638 square feet of office/professional space and 24,000 square feet of warehouse space (all on the lower level in the rear of the Property) on a 3.21-acre parcel of land.‚Äã The Heights Professional Medical Plaza was originally constructed in 1975 and significantly renovated in 2021 and 2022, including a new roof with a 20-year warranty (contact the agent for more details).‚Äã The Heights Professional Medical Plaza is 100% leased and is improved by a complimentary mix of local, regional, and national tenants offering products and services for the surrounding community.‚Äã

The Heights Professional Medical Plaza is situated along Southwest Highway (IL Route 7), one of the area‚Äôs primary commercial and commuter corridors.‚Äã The property enjoys outstanding frontage, visibility, and signage and benefits from two points of access.‚Äã The primary point of access for the plaza is positioned at a traffic light along Southwest Highway.‚Äã The plaza also boasts a digital sign at the signalized entrance that can be seen by oncoming traffic from both directions.‚Äã The Heights Professional Medical Plaza is surrounded by commercial and medical tenants and is well located in the northwest corner of the city.‚Äã The Property offers convenient access to two Metra Stations, several highways and Interstate 294.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
DIVERSE TENANT MIX: Heights Professional Medical Plaza benefits from a diverse mix of local, regional, and national tenants that provide a variety of goods and services to the surrounding community.

RENTAL INCREASES & RE TAX REIMBURSEMENTS: A majority of the tenants at Heights Professional Medical Plaza have scheduled annual rent increases throughout their primary lease terms. Additionally, a Majority of the leases also call for the tenants to reimburse any increases in real estate taxes above their respective base years, providing a steady increase in income and an attractive hedge against inflation.

STRATEGIC LOCATION: Situated at a signalized intersection of Southwest Highway and 117th Street, the Heights Professional Medical Plaza is well located along one of the area‚Äôs primary commercial and commuter corridors. The Property is surrounded by commercial buildings and medical facilities and is positioned in between two Metra Stations, Palos Heights (0.6-miles away) and Palos Park (0.8-miles away). The Property is approximately 2.5 miles from US Highway 45, 3-miles from US Highway 20 and 3.5-miles from Interstate 294. The Heights Professional Medical Plaza is also less than 2.5-miles from Moraine Valley Community College and Trinity Christian College. Additionally, the area surrounding Southwest Highway is home to densely populated residential neighborhoods with a built-in customer base for the tenants occupying the plaza.

GROWING MEDICAL OFFICE PRESENCE: The Property is well positioned in the northwest corner of Palos Heights. This portion of town is quickly becoming the destination for medical facilities and tenants. The Heights Professional Medical Plaza is across the street from the High Tech Medical Park and seconds from the Southwest Highway Physician Center. The Property is also just 1-mile from Northwest Medicine Palos Hospital, a 425-bed hospital with more than 600 physicians on staff, representing 42 medical specialties. Additionally, W College Drive (just south of the Property) is home to several medical facilities.

FRONTAGE, VISIBILITY & SIGNAGE: The Heights Professional Medical Plaza enjoys outstanding frontage (approximately 585 linear feet), visibility and signage along Southwest Highway (IL Route 7). The Property has two points of access, and the primary entrance and exit are positioned at a signalized intersection. Additionally, the monument sign is positioned at the intersection and features a digital sign that can be seen from both directions by oncoming traffic.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: More than 20,600 vehicles pass the Property each day along Southwest Highway (IL Route 7).

OUTSTANDING DEMOGRAPHICS: 74,200+ people live within a 3-mile radius of the Property with an average household income of $93,170. An impressive 227,200+ people live within a 5-mile radius of the Property. Additionally, there are more than 91,900 employees within a 5-mile radius of the property.

LONG TERM ANCHOR TENANT - Dollar General has had continued presence at the center since 2005, exercising several lease extensions along the way, speaking to the tenant's strong commitment and belief in this location.

This site is located up the street from McDonald's, Walgreens and Advance Auto Parts. The strip center takes advantage of robust traffic counts from nearby local and major national tenants such as Family Dollar, Food Lion, O'Reilly Auto Parts, Burger King, Sheetz, Pizza Hut, Subway, Little Caesars, Wendy's, McDonald's, Dairy Queen, and many, many others.

marketingDescription:
For 57 years, its customers included actor Paul Newman, race car driver Kyle Petty, industry titans, I-94 travelers between Detroit and Chicago looking for a great meal, and area residents celebrating special occasions.‚Äã¬† Gilbert‚Äôs Steakhouse has been a landmark in Mid-Michigan for three generations.‚Äã¬† The historic restaurant was known for its many ‚ÄúTiffany‚Äù style lamps & other antiques situated throughout the restaurant, banquet hall and bar.‚Äã¬† There is a fireplace in the lobby, and another in ‚ÄúThe Cabin Bar,‚Äù which was originally a log home.‚Äã¬† The building has been expanded several times to the state-of-the-art structure that exists today.‚Äã¬† It truly has ‚Äúone of a kind‚Äù ambiance.‚Äã

¬†

In 2004, newspaper headlines in Jackson blared ‚ÄúEnd of an Era‚Äù to describe how locals felt about the closing of this ‚Äúarea‚Äù institution.‚Äã¬† Patrons waited in 2 hour lines to hug the owner goodbye & wish him well.‚Äã¬† The current owner has since invested more than $1,250,000 in renovating the property, including new roof, gutters, electrical system, HVAC, kitchen equipment, tables and chairs, mahogany paneling, granite bar tops, carpet, restrooms, etc.‚Äã¬† The entire property was gutted and rebuilt to today‚Äôs standards, but it maintains the elegant charm and ambience of the historic Gilbert‚Äôs.‚Äã

¬†

Current Condition:

The building has been vacant for several years, during which time a truck hit the port cochere and damaged the corner of it.‚Äã¬† There was a storm in the summer of 2021 that caused some leaks in the roof; they are currently being repaired.‚Äã¬† Some of the restaurant equipment has been sold.‚Äã¬† Most of the antiques and Tiffany lamps have been sold.‚Äã¬† The restaurant is still fundamentally sound and beautiful and ready to be ‚Äúrecreated‚Äù into a new concept.‚Äã

¬†
investmentHighlights: The restaurant is surrounded by five nationally branded hotels, none of which have kitchen facilities or meeting rooms. Not only is there tremendous opportunity for catering and banquets, but the hotels provide nearly 1,000 guests on a daily basis that are looking for a good place to eat. This is truly an extraordinary and unique opportunity.

investmentHighlights:
ASSET: The Fountains at Town Center is an 11-tenant retail center constructed in 2006. The Property consists of two well maintained and attractive retail buildings totaling 27,050 square feet with three points of access, abundant parking. The 3.27-acre parcel offers outstanding visibility and frontage along W Lies Road.

STRATEGIC LOCATION: The highly visible Property is strategically located along W Lies Road, one of the region‚Äôs primary commuter corridors, and is 500 feet from the signalized intersection with N Gary Avenue. N Gary Avenue connects the Property with W Army Trail Road to the north and North Avenue to the south, and also is the western boundary of a large business and industrial district in between the two major retail corridors. The Property is close to national retailers, large-scale shopping centers and densely developed residential neighborhoods.

BUILT-IN CUSTOMER BASE: In addition to the densely developed neighborhoods nearby, the Property is positioned at the entrance to The Fountains at Town Center, a town home community built in the mid 2010's by Town and Country Homes. The Fountains at Town Center features 145 beautifully constructed town houses with floor plans ranging from 2,107 to 2,548 square feet of living space.

PROMINENT ACCESS AND VISIBILITY: The Property is located at the at the intersection of W Lies Road and Fountain View Drive with outstanding visibility and frontage along both. The beautifully maintained and landscaped center lines both sides of Fountain View Drive and also serves as a formal entryway to the abutting Fountains at Town Center luxury residential community.

ATTRACTIVE RENT ROLL: The Property is currently 92.07% leased to an attractive mix of tenants (including four restaurants, a hair salon, a nail salon, a dry cleaner, and a liquor store) that serve the surrounding community and draw traffic to the property. The center has 2,145 square feet of vacant space (two suites), that offer the opportunity to add value via lease up.

SCHEDULED RENT INCREASES: Five of the Tenants have scheduled rent increases in either their primary lease terms, or at the start of each of their option periods providing a steady increase in income and an attractive hedge against inflation.

ECONOMIC TRADE AREA: The Property is just seconds from a large industrial/business district located between N Gary Avenue and Schmale Road. The large business and industrial parks are home to more than 100 businesses including Ingram Micro, Assa Abloy, FIC America Corp, Demar Logistics, Inc, FIC America Corp, UPS, Owens & Minor, International Paper, Prinova USA, USPS Regional Center, Benjamin Moore Manufacturing Facility, Office Depot Manufacturing Facility, and Beacon Building Products. These businesses employ thousands of people and are just seconds away from The Property.

IMPRESSIVE DEMOGRAPHICS: Over 102,000 people live within 3-miles of the Property with an average household income of $115,361. An impressive 250,700 people live within 5-miles of the Property with an average household income of approximately $122,075. Additionally, there are more than 47,200 employees within 3-miles of the Property.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: Approximately 9,800 vehicles pass by the Property each day along W Lies Road. More than 32,800 vehicles per day pass through the adjacent intersection of W Lies Road and N Gary Avenue.

DUPAGE COUNTY: Carol Stream is located in DuPage County, which has considerably less tax exposure than neighboring Cook County. This makes it a more desired sub-market for Chicago commercial real estate. DuPage County has over 1,092,400 residents with an average household income of $131,242 producing strong spending power in Carol Stream and the surrounding communities.

marketingDescription:
PRICE DROPPED $300K Make Offer Now!

A Prime 13-Unit Neighborhood Shopping Center in Citrus County, Florida with Lake View!

3451 E Louise Lane/ Hwy 200, Hernando, FL 34442

We're proud to offer the 200 Plaza, a 13-unit, 25,500 SF CBS Neighborhood Shopping Center situated within the Citrus County Submarket of the Tampa/St Petersburg MSA.‚Äã Occupying an entire city block on a 3.27-acre lot zoned as General Neighborhood Commercial (GNC), it boasts a stable tenant mix of local businesses.‚Äã With over 632‚Äô of highway frontage on SR 200, it ensures full ingress and egress on N Carl G Rose Hwy (11,300 AADT), just north of the controlled intersection of US 41 N (9,500 AADT).‚Äã The center offers 71 well-lit surface parking spaces (2.8/1,000 SF NRA) and houses a diverse range of tenants currently occupying 89% if the building, from professional offices to retail establishments and beauty services.‚Äã¬† The center's prime location places it amidst flourishing communities like Inverness, Crystal River, Citrus Springs, Beverly Hills, Lecanto, and Ocala.‚Äã Citrus County, home to 153,600 residents, is primed for growth with potential expansion up to 350k residents under the county‚Äôs LDC.‚Äã With infrastructure developments underway to accommodate an expected 30,000 new residents by 2030 and boasting the 3rd highest number of vacant parcels (61,000) in Florida, it's a hotspot for development.‚Äã Furthermore, its position within the Tampa‚ÄìSt.‚Äã Petersburg‚ÄìClearwater MSA, the 18th largest in the U.‚ÄãS.‚Äã, underscores its significance in the nation's premier real estate market.‚Äã

Logistic Details:

County Road 486 runs entirely along West Norvell Bryant Highway.‚Äã It runs West to East from SR 44 east of Crystal River into US-41 in Hernando, just south of the southern terminus of SR 200.‚Äã The route was once former SR 486.‚Äã County Road 486 spans 4 lanes, is almost entirely a divided highway, and is flanked by a parallel bicycle path on the south side.‚Äã¬†¬†

County Road 491 is Lecanto Highway, a bi-county South to North road that begins at the Hernando-Citrus County Line in Oak Grove near the Withlacoochee State Forest, and ends at SR 200 in Stoke's Ferry, just south of the intersection with the northern segment of CR 39.‚Äã It was formerly designated as SR 491.‚Äã¬†

County Road 44 (often marked as County Road 44W) exists as the western tip of old Florida State Road 44, south of "Downtown" Crystal River.‚Äã The suffix "W" was most likely added to not confuse this section with State Road 44, to the north, and to show its location by being west of US 19 and US 98(SR 55).‚Äã ¬† As with the majority of these type of 'coastal spur' routes, in West Central Florida, it is county maintained.‚Äã¬†¬†

U.‚Äã S.‚Äã Route 19 (US-19) runs 264 miles (425 km) along Florida's West Coast from an interchange with U.‚Äã S.‚Äã Route 41 in Memphis, Florida, south of Tampa, and continues to the Georgia border north of Monticello, Florida.‚Äã Newly 6 lane Hwy constructed from Hernando County line to Fort Island Trail and US 19 in Crystal River, Florida.‚Äã¬†

Suncoast Parkway:¬†

The Suncoast Parkway recently opened was a of $135 Million Dollar expansion which extends 13 miles north from US-98 to SR 44 which features 15 new bridges, electronic tolling gantries and the extension of The Suncoast Trail part of the Florida's Statewide Greenways and Trail System.‚Äã The Suncoast Parkway is just 68 Miles 1 hour and 15 mins¬† from Tampa making it a great commuting Highway for workforce seeking to be outside of the Tampa traffic.‚Äã The Veterans Expressway and Suncoast Parkway is a north‚Äìsouth toll road near the Florida Gulf Coast.‚Äã Maintained and operated by Florida's Turnpike Enterprise, this 68-mile transportation corridor extends from State Road 60 in Tampa, north to State Road 44 near Lecanto.‚Äã

Citrus County Makeup:¬†

Citrus County is a predominantly residential region.‚Äã With over one-third of all residents in the county being senior citizens, the healthcare sector is an important source of revenue for the local economy.‚Äã Numerous hospitals and healthcare centers are scattered throughout the region, including Citrus Memorial Hospital, Seven Rivers Regional Medical Center, and Citrus Endoscopy and Surgery Center.‚Äã Citrus Memorial Hospital is among the largest employers in the region and with a 204-bed acute care facility.‚Äã Other prominent employers in Citrus County include Citrus County School District and Cypress Creek Academy in the census-designated place of Lecanto.‚Äã

Citrus County Growth:

Citrus County, Florida's estimated population is 155,582 with a growth rate of 1.29% in the past year according to the most recent United States census data.‚Äã Citrus County, Florida is the 34th largest county in Florida.‚Äã The 2010 Population was 141,173 and has seen a growth of 10.21% since this time.‚Äã ¬† Citrus County current LDC allows for approximately a population of 350k residencies.‚Äã Given the expansion of the Suncoast Parkway and the 6 lane expansion of US 19 we are in the path of tremendous growth.‚Äã ¬† Currently Citrus County has 60,000 vacant parcels of land prime for development.‚Äã ¬† The County and incorporated Cities have plans for extensive utility expansion throughout the county including the expansion of the Crystal River Airport Run Way 5000 feet to allow for larger aircraft to land and take off including a newly funded 75 acres industrial complex granted by the state to expand utilities, road reconstruction to support eighteen wheelers and to include environmentally friendly and energy conservation features.‚Äã¬†¬†¬†

Community Development:¬†

  • ‚Äã

    957 single-family residential homes on a 354-acre site in Lecanto.‚Äã¬†¬†

  • ‚Äã

    500-lot subdivision, located in Citrus Springs by Habitat for Humanity of Citrus County.‚Äã¬†¬†¬†

  • ‚Äã

    Green Mills Group 2020 built a 106-unit apartment campus offering affordable housing on Colonnade Street in Inverness.‚Äã¬†¬†

  • ‚Äã

    County commissioners approved a planned unit development (PUD) for Preservation Point RV Resort, a 234-acre property.‚Äã¬†¬†

  • ‚Äã

    Jaymelday Holdings LLC calls for up to 600 RV sites and amenities such as a pool, golf cart rentals, bar and grill, basketball court, and walking trails in Crystal River.‚Äã¬†¬†¬†

  • ‚Äã

    207 Home subdivision by DR Horton in Beverly Hills, Florida Citrus Ridge Area.‚Äã¬†¬†

  • ‚Äã

    930 Unit Subdivision in Planning with a national builder in Lecanto just off the Suncoast Parkway extension on SR 44.‚Äã¬†¬†¬†

marketingDescription:
Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to purchase the mixed-use investment property located at 54 S 4th Avenue in Mount Vernon, New York (the ‚ÄúProperty‚Äù).‚Äã The three-story building contains two (2) retail units at street-level and two (2) vacant commercial units on the upper floors.‚Äã These units do not currently have a certificate of occupancy and will require renovations to bring them online and ready for lease up.‚Äã The building has 11,100 square feet of living area and sits on a 0.18-acre corner parcel of land.‚Äã The Property features an ample parking lot with access along S 5th Avenue, one space of which is rented to Rent-A-Center for overflow parking.‚Äã

54 S 4th Avenue is well-located in the heart of downtown Mt Vernon.‚Äã The Property is one block from 1st Street and Gramatan Avenue, the area‚Äôs primary commercial corridors, and offers a highly walkable neighborhood with numerous area amenities for residents including dining, entertainment, and retail options.‚Äã The Property also offers a transit-oriented location; it is 400 feet from a bus stop with service on three different lines, is 0.3-miles from the Mount Vernon East Metro North Train Station (New Haven Line), 0.9-miles from the Mt Vernon West Metro North Station (Harlem Line) and 1-mile from the 241st Street Subway Station (Red-Line).‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
COMMERCIAL LEASES: The Property is improved by two (2) ground floor commercial units that total 6,500 square feet. The US Army Recruiting Center leases 3,250 square feet and has 2-years remaining on their 5-year lease extension. The lease is backed by the US Government.

The Meat Market leases 3,250 square feet and has a 9+ years remaining on their lease with one (1), 10-year renewal option. The lease calls for attractive rent increases every 2 years throughout the primary lease term and renewal option. Also, the Meat Market utilizes 5,000 square feet of basement space that is not included in their stated unit size. This space is equipped with freezers, equipment, and a loading dock.

Rent-A-Center leases one space in the parking lot in the rear of the Property which has entry and egress along S 5th Avenue.

VACANT COMMERCIAL UNITS: The Property is improved by vacant commercial space on the second and third floors. The units are off-line and will require a capital investment and renovations to make them tenant ready.

DENSELY POPULATED, DOWNTOWN LOCATION: Over 72,400+ people live within 1 mile of the Property with an average household income over $96,305. An impressive 414,300+ people live within 3 miles of the Property with an average household income of $122,000. Additionally, there are more than 107,100 employees within 3 miles of the Property.

54 S 4th Avenue is located in the heart of downtown Mt Vernon, which features numerous dining, entertainment, and retail options for residents. The Empire City Casino, the Yonkers Raceway, and the Cross County Shopping Center, with more than 80 shops and restaurants, are all approximately 2-miles away.

TRANSIT ORIENTED PROPERTY: The Property is 400 feet from a bus stop with service on four different lines (0042, 0052, 0053), is 0.3-miles from the Mount Vernon East Metro North Train Station (New Haven Line), 0.9-miles from the Mt Vernon West Metro North Station (Harlem Line) and 1-mile from the 241st Street Subway Station (Red-Line). The property is also 1-mile from the Bronx River Expressway and Cross County Parkway, and 2-miles from Interstate 87.

VALUE-ADD OPPORTUNITY: The Meat Market is currently on a gross lease; however, they will begin reimbursing their pro-rata share (25%) of the annual real estate taxes beginning in year 3 of their 10-year lease. This will represent a significant increase in the overall income of the Property.

The Property has vacant commercial space on the second and third floors (2,300 SF per floor), and offers the opportunity to update and lease up the spaces, providing a significant increase in the overall income of the Property. The units are off-line and will require a capital investment and renovations to make them tenant ready.

Additionally, the opportunity may exist in the future to convert the second and third floors into four (4) 1-Bedroom/1-Bathroom residential units. This type of conversion will require cooperation with the city‚Äôs building and zoning departments, but would offer the ability to capture part of Mount Vernon residential market, which is highly sought after.

STRONG RENTAL MARKET: Mt Vernon features a very strong rental market with excellent proximity to New York City and numerous prominent area employers including three large Hospitals (with more than 1,000 total beds) within 4-miles, creating high demand and low vacancy. The Property is also just 2-miles from Sarah Lawrence College.
