description: Ultimate Flexibility, Value Add Grocery Shadow Anchored Shopping Center in Medford, OR
marketingDescription:
NAI Elliott, as exclusive advisor, is pleased to offer for sale Shamrock Square, a 13,750 square foot value add retail center located in the economic hub of southern Oregon: Medford.‚Äã The property boasts a prime location at the intersection of Crater Lake Ave and Stevens Street across from Chase Bank to the west and Safeway and Rite Aid to the southwest.‚Äã To the north is the Providence Medford Medical Center, a 168-bed hospital built in 1985 with 600,000+ square feet of building area sprawling 30+ acres.‚Äã

Shamrock Square was built in 1960 on 1.19 acres and is divided into three buildings on three tax parcels that vary in size.‚Äã The property currently functions as one single center with no existing covenants, conditions, and restrictions (CC&Rs) among the buildings.‚Äã The asphalt paved parking lot has 81 parking spaces with six access points and monument signage.‚Äã There are 50 apartments units bordering the subject property to the northeast and a single-family home abutting the property to the east.‚Äã Secondary access is provided to the apartments via an alley north of the property.‚Äã

The property provides unparalleled exit strategies due to a variety of factors.‚Äã First, it is already separated into three distinct tax lots per building, thereby allowing future ownership to segment the real estate per their business plan.‚Äã Second, current rents average $13.59 per square foot full service, allowing both conversion to triple net leases and additional lift to market rates ranging $18.00 - $30.00 per square foot triple net, depending on the unit.‚Äã Third, average tenant tenure is 12.37 years at the property, allowing an investor to negotiate leases for longer terms and higher rents without releasing risk.‚Äã Last, market alternatives for owner users and comparable retail development are extremely limited.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
1.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Shamrock Square Dominates the Competition in Investor Exit Strategies:

a.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† NNN Lease Conversions. Current property ownership has signed full services leases with all tenants. Consequently, there is a 41% expense slippage that may be recaptured with lease renegotiations.

b.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† 157% Market-to-Market Redevelopment Rents. Existing rents at the shopping center range from $11.54 - $20.00 per sq. ft. full service annually (avg. $13.59/sf). Meanwhile, market alternatives in the immediate trade area range from $18.00 - $30.00 per sq. ft. triple net. These retailers share the same traffic and demographic base.

c.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Existing Parcel Boundaries Enable Segmented Future Resale. Shamrock Square currently operates as one cohesive shopping center, yet existing parcel boundaries separate the Property into three distinct units. Future ownership benefits from the exit flexibility of marketing these parcels for sale separately.

d.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Short Term Leases Create Business Plan Flexibility. All leases expire December 31, 2023. However, tenant tenures range from 2-29 years at the property (12.37 years, on average), and most tenants have requested 3-5 years extensions. Alternatively, future ownership may let the leases expire and execute their business plan per their timeline.

e.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Zero Competing Owner User Alternatives. There is presently no comparable owner user opportunity in the Medford market. Also, because the buildings already exist on separate tax lots, there is an ability to own and operate a portion of the property independent from the rest (see Appendix A for details).

f.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Zero Development Alternatives. There are no competing properties for sale with comparably strong retail fundamentals to Shamrock Square. With all leases set to expire December 31, 2023, a developer may t renegotiate leases terms as needed to cover carry costs during the entitlement period.

2.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Neighborhood Amenities Create Long-term Value. Shamrock Square benefits from immediate exposure to secondary traffic visiting the Providence Medford Medical Center, a 168-bed hospital north of the property, and the Medford Center, a 415,105 sq. ft. power center anchored by T.J. Maxx, Ross, Burlington, and Safeway southwest of the property.

3.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† High Visibility, High Synergy Signalized Intersection. Shamrock Square is situated at the northeast corner of a high visibility intersection across from Safeway and Chase Bank. The property has unobstructed views from all directions and benefits from the draw of daily needs traffic.

4.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Epicenter of Southern Oregon Commerce. Medford, OR serves as the center of commerce for southern Oregon. Costco, two Walmart Supercenters, T.J. Maxx, Marshalls, Burlington, Home Depot, Lowe‚Äôs Home Improvement, etc. ‚Äì all dominant, national retailers have established a presence to capture the ~400,000 residents in the greater trade area who converge for shopping, dining, recreation, and entertainment.

The Property features a diverse tenant mix with anchors that include Big Sandy, Dollar Tree, Dunham‚Äôs Sports, B2 Outlet, Shoe Sensation, Starbucks and T-Mobile.‚Äã Other tenants include Bath & Body Works, Sally Beauty, Rent-A-Center, Cost Cutters, Game Stop, and Little Mexico, etc.‚Äã The center has a history of strong occupancy and operating history.‚Äã

The Klink Group of Marcus & Millichap is pleased to present a compelling investment opportunity in Muncie, Indiana, showcasing a strategically situated property with remarkable potential for redevelopment.‚Äã The property currently occupied by Family Dollar, contributing to a reliable stream of rental income giving a new owner flexibility with their redevelopment plan as the property is currently providing income.‚Äã What sets this property apart is its zoning, which allows for a versatile range of applications, including retail, self-storage, and various industrial uses.‚Äã¬† The property sits on over 4.75 acres of land providing ample opportunity to continue building new structures onto the property in addition to the existing 47,344 sq ft building.‚Äã

This property offers an enticing combination of location, income stability from Family Dollar, and diverse usage potential.‚Äã Its strategic position in Muncie provides easy access to major transportation routes, making it an attractive choice for businesses seeking to establish a presence in the local market or streamline distribution operations.‚Äã Furthermore, Muncie has experienced consistent population growth in recent years, driven by its affordability and quality of life, which bodes well for the property's value and its appeal to a wide array of businesses.‚Äã¬† Given the close proximity to Ball Sate University which is a major economic driver for the city of Muncie, the property could provide a redevelopment opportunity that caters to any existing need of the University.‚Äã

The zoning is a noteworthy attribute as it accommodates a wide range of various business uses, this adaptability opens the door to a multitude of development strategies, including leasing the existing retail space, repurposing sections of the building & property into self-storage units to meet the growing demand in the area, or exploring the potential for an industrial facility to cater to local and regional logistics and distribution needs.‚Äã

marketingDescription:
Cushman & Wakefield‚Äôs Retail Investment Advisors, as exclusive advisors, are pleased to present the opportunity to acquire Rolling Hills Square (the ‚ÄúProperty‚Äù), a 107,102 square foot value-add grocery anchored shopping center featuring Fry‚Äôs Food & Drug (Kroger) as anchor and Oak Street Health (Recently acquired by CVS), located on the southwest corner of Kolb Road and Golf Links Road in Tucson, Arizona.‚Äã

The Property is situated on approximately 11.5 acres of land in the southern portion of Tucson Metropolitan Area.‚Äã Rolling Hills Square is currently 86.9% leased to an assortment of complimentary ‚Äòdaily-needs‚Äô tenants offering grocery, cellular, tax preparation, salons and spa, urgent care, along with several dining options.‚Äã

The tenant roster is led by Fry‚Äôs Food and Drug (Kroger), which is Arizona‚Äôs dominant grocer and one of the nineteen brands owned by the Kroger Co.‚Äã Family of Stores (NYSE: KR).‚Äã Kroger is the largest supermarket in the United States by revenue.‚Äã Fry's Food & Drug has been operating at this location since 1980, and their lease runs through February 2031, with eight, five-year options.‚Äã Other notable tenants include Oak Street Health, Verizon Wireless, The UPS Store, H&R Block and Banner Urgent Care to name a few.‚Äã

The Property is ideally located at the intersection of Kolb Road and Golf Links Road, with excellent frontage, visibility and traffic counts.‚Äã Approximately 41,628 vehicles pass the Property daily along Golf Links Road, and another 45,140 vehicles pass along Kolb Road.‚Äã

Rolling Hills Square is located within close proximity to Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, Arizona‚Äôs second largest active air force base, approximately 1 mile away.‚Äã Encompassing over 10,000 acres, Davis-Monthan Air Force Base is home to approximately 6,500 Active Duty military personnel, 1,000 Reserve and Air National Guard personnel, and 3,000 civilian employees.‚Äã

Tucson, Arizona retail market has delivered 239K SF with a 12 month net absorption of 362K SF.‚Äã The vacancy rate is 5.6%, with retail rents rising 1.6% in the past 12 months.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
ANCHORED BY THE LARGEST GROCER IN ARIZONA

Fry's Food and Drug is the largest grocer in Arizona with approximately 127 stores. The Fry‚Äôs Food and Drug at Rolling Hills Square has been operating at this location since 1980, and their lease runs through February 2031, with eight, five-year options. Fry‚Äôs Food & Drug is part of the Kroger Company (NYSE: KR). The Kroger Company is the country‚Äôs largest supermarket chain by revenue. Kroger operates, either directly or through its subsidiaries, 24 supermarkets and multi-department stores.


VALUE ADD WITH UPSIDE POTENTIAL

There is multiple opportunities for upside through lease up of 14,008 SF as well as developing at least one more pad site. The development of a potential single tenant building or a multitenant building at the northwest portion of the Property and potential for development of pad directly north of grocer (not modeled and viability to be confirmed by buyer). See site plan for details.


ACCESSIBILITY AND STRONG TRAFFIC COUNTS

There are a total of seven ingress/egress access points to Rolling Hills Square. In addition, both arterials to the Property offer strong traffic counts with over 41,000 vehicles passing the Property per day on Golf Links Road and over 45,000 on Kolb Road.


PROXIMITY TO DAVIS-MONTHAN AIR FORCE BASE

Approximately 1 mile west lies Arizona's second largest active air force base. Encompassing over 10,000 acres, Davis-Monthan Air Force Base is home to approximately 6,500 Active Duty military personnel, 1,000 Reserve and Air National Guard personnel, and 3,000 civilian employees.

marketingDescription:
SHOP Companies has been retained to exclusively offer for sale Uptown Center, a 65% occupied 187,467 square foot shopping center on over 14 acres located at the northwest corner of SE 15th Street & Midwest Boulevard in Midwest City, Oklahoma.‚Äã The property, never before having been offered for sale by the family who developed it originally, offers an unprecedented chance for commercial real estate investors seeking untapped potential and growth.‚Äã Priced at under $50.00/SF and at under $15.00/SF to the land, this investment opportunity stands out for its unique history, strategic location, and attractive pricing.‚Äã

The shopping center captures the essence of Midwest City's retail heritage ‚Äì positioned at the edge of Midwest City‚Äôs Original Mile, designated as ‚ÄúAmerica‚Äôs Model City‚Äù for post-war community development.‚Äã In 1951, The Original Mile Historic District, became the first residential neighborhood in Oklahoma to be identified as a historic district and recommended for listing in the National Register of Historic Places.‚Äã

Currently home to regional and national tenants like Locke Supply, Sherwin Williams, Family Dollar, and Goodwill, Uptown Center offers both a prominent tenant mix and ample expansion opportunities.‚Äã Beyond the in-place income, the property's true value lies in its redevelopment potential.‚Äã With visionary insight, the shopping center can be transformed into a modern hub, aligning with evolving consumer trends and preferences.‚Äã Existing infrastructure combined with strategic redesign offers an ideal canvas for a dynamic, community-centric space.‚Äã

Developers can also leverage public financing incentives to stimulate local economic growth.‚Äã Midwest City has a track record of partnering with developers to provide various financing options, tax incentives, and grants to catalyze transformative redevelopment, underscoring the city's commitment to nurturing business expansion and elevating the property's investment appeal.‚Äã

The property's location just one mile from both Tinker Air Force Base and Town Center Plaza further enhances its redevelopment viability.‚Äã Tinker AFB, with over 30,000 military and civilian employees, contributes over $3.5 billion annually to the local economy while Town Center Plaza, a thriving regional power/lifestyle center spanning nearly 700,000 square feet on approximately 90 acres, adds further value by creating a dynamic shopping ecosystem within the local trade area.‚Äã

    Redevelopment Potential: Transform Uptown Center into a modern retail hub, catering to evolving needs and invigorating community growth.

    Public Financing Support: Tap into public financing incentives, bolstered by Midwest City's commitment to economic expansion.

  • ‚Äã

    Strategic Location: Uptown Center's proximity to Tinker AFB's 30,000-strong workforce and thriving Town Center Plaza ensures sustained demand.

  • ‚Äã

    Compelling Pricing: Priced under $50.00/SF, a fraction of replacement cost, Uptown Center offers outstanding investment value and upside potential.

marketingDescription:
Wilmington City Market

Situated in the heart of the Central Business District in Historic Downtown Wilmington, the Old-Wilmington City Market benefits from exceptional visibility with frontage on two arterial thoroughfares characterized by high pedestrian and moderate vehicular traffic.‚Äã Established in 1887, this meticulously preserved property spans approximately 14,700 +/- square feet and has served as a critical retail hub in downtown Wilmington with an Annual Gross Income of over $210,000.‚Äã

The property's prime location‚Äîadjacent to the Riverwalk and in close proximity to an array of boutique hotels, upscale dining establishments, specialty shopping, and vibrant nightlife‚Äîoffers an unparalleled investment opportunity in the burgeoning Front Street district south of Market.‚Äã Given its strategic position and size, the property is exceptionally well-suited for continuation as a boutique retail center, covered land play or re imagined through the many possible redevelopment options.‚Äã

Architecturally designed to emulate a miniature downtown street scape, the Old-Wilmington City Market features a variety of shops surrounding a central atrium.‚Äã Its enduring allure and strategic placement have enabled numerous tenants to achieve sustained commercial success, with some maintaining a business presence at the location for over two decades.‚Äã This testament to its viability makes the property not merely a Downtown Wilmington landmark but also a paragon for retail success.‚Äã

Furthermore, the Central Business District (CBD) zoning designation affords flexibility for a broad range of applications and re development opportunities.‚Äã Removal of Contributing Historic Structure Status was applied for and granted.‚Äã

Please Note Seller has development renderings of possible future re development ideas for this location.‚Äã Renderings are for idea generations purposes only, no representation or warranties express or implied.‚Äã

Showing remarks

We kindly invite you to visit the property during standard business hours of 10:00 AM to 6:00 PM.‚Äã However, we respectfully request that you refrain from discussing any matters related to the sale or expressions of interest with current tenants.‚Äã Should you wish to schedule a private viewing outside of regular business hours, please coordinate directly with the listing agent.‚Äã Be advised that the listing agent will be present for all scheduled showings conducted during off-hours to provide necessary oversight and information.‚Äã

marketingDescription:
RIPCO REAL ESTATE has been retained on an exclusive basis to arrange for the sale of 68-100 Old Riverhead Rd in Westhampton Beach, NY (the 'Property').‚Äã

The Property is improved by the Northmall Shopping Center, a 25,000 SF shopping center occupied by a mix of tenants providing neighborhood necessities to the surrounding area.‚Äã The property spans across two buildings and three acres with ~80 lined parking spaces, located in front and rear of the center.‚Äã

Situated along Old Riverhead Road, the Property provides fantastic exposure and accessibility along one of the Hampton's main thoroughfares.‚Äã The Property is ~85% occupied providing immediate cash flow while also having a significant amount of upside.‚Äã Aside from the center's strong, long-standing local tenants, Sherwin Williams has recently singed a long-term lease and is in the final stages of their build-out.‚Äã

Old Riverhead Road is the main road that leads in and out of the town of Westhampton Beach and also leads directly to Dune Road, home to some of Long Island's most luxurious beachfront real estate.‚Äã Less than a mile north on Old Riverhead Road, is Francis Gabreski Airport, which services both civilian and military uses, and The Hampton Business District, which is the East End‚Äôs first and only Class A business park.‚Äã

Westhampton Beach is a Village within the Town of Southampton located just 80 miles east of Manhattan.‚Äã Like the rest of Long Island‚Äôs east end, Westhampton is a popular weekend and summer destination for New York‚Äôs affluent.‚Äã Renowned for its pristine Atlantic Ocean Beaches and boating opportunities, Westhampton Beach is the epitome of luxury living.‚Äã Westhampton Beach has a population of 2,200 with an average household income of ~$170,000.‚Äã The Hamptons, primarily known as a popular summer destination, is no longer just a seasonal destination.‚Äã Over the past few years, Long Island‚Äôs east end has enjoyed an influx in their year-round population.‚Äã Similarly, the property doesn‚Äôt solely serve the summer crowd; while still benefiting from the heightened summer months, the shopping center is a neighborhood staple, serving the locals year-round.‚Äã

Please reach out to the exclusive brokers brokers for additional information or to arrange a property tour.‚Äã

marketingDescription: Mid-America Real Estate Corporation has been retained on behalf of the owner to sell the 100% fee simple interest in Village Green Shopping Center, a 93% leased neighborhood center serving the highly affluent and dense infill near north suburbs of Chicago.‚Äã Download the OM: http://properties.‚Äãmidamericagrp.‚Äãcom/Village-Green-Shopping-Center-Park-Ridge
investmentHighlights:
DYNAMIC MIX OF SERVICE-ORIENTED TENANTS
Village Green is 93% leased to an attractive lineup of specialty retail, service, health & wellness, and restaurant uses. The tenant mix creates daily customer draws and offers substantial protection against any e-commerce exposure. National and regional brands such as BMO, Lou Malnati‚Äôs, Goldfish Swim School, Wheel & Sprocket, Midwest Orthopaedics, Westside Children‚Äôs Therapy, BFT, FedEx Office, and Subway comprise over 68% of the total gross revenue at Village Green.

DESTINATION SUBURBAN DOWNTOWN
Village Green is located less than one mile northwest of downtown Park Ridge, one of Chicago‚Äôs most successful suburban downtowns that has seen extraordinary growth and development in recent years. Centered at Northwest Highway and Touhy Avenue, downtown Park Ridge features an abundance of high-end restaurants, trendy boutiques, and entertainment venues including the historic Art Deco Pickwick Theatre all in a walkable area centered around the downtown Park Ridge Metra train station.

DENSE & AFFLUENT NEAR NORTH DEMOGRAPHICS
Park Ridge features one of the most dense and affluent suburban markets in Chicago. Given its proximity to the city and O‚ÄôHare International Airport (2nd busiest US airport), Park Ridge provides a uniquely convenient residential location for many commuters to both the CBD and airport for business travel. Within a three-mile radius of the subject offering, there are 162,240 residents with an average household income of $123,690.

HIGH-TRAFFIC, VISIBLE LOCATION | PROXIMITY TO MAJOR HIGHWAY SYSTEMS
Outstanding visibility and both local and regional accessibility from the major thoroughfares of Park Ridge. Additionally, the center is located one mile east of I-294 (Tri-State Tollway), and two miles north of I-90 (Jane Addams Memorial Tollway). Local transportation is offered by the Metra Northwest Line (401,000 riders per year), with the Park Ridge and Dee Road train stations located along Busse Highway, both within a mile of the center. The CTA Bus Route 209 offering access to the CTA Blue Line train.

RECENT LEASING VELOCITY
Village Green has experienced significant leasing velocity in 2023; Body Fit Training Fitness Studio, Dermani MedSpa, and Westside Childrens Therapy each signed a new 10-year lease. Recent renewals have also been completed with Subway and Nail Beauty.

VALUE-ADD OPPORTUNITIES
The property features an opportunity to add value by leasing up the remaining vacant spaces at market rental rates resulting in a potential $150,000 of additional gross income. Village Green has a competitive advantage to attract new tenants given the relatively lower rents compared to Downtown Park Ridge. Additionally, a buyer could employ a parcelization strategy that could create cap rate arbitrage by separately parceling the BMO branch and ATM and selling off into the single tenant market at an attractive cap rate.

marketingDescription:
‚ÄúConstantine the Great‚Äù a Screenplay Written and to Be Directed by Award Winning Director/writer/producer/composer/songwriter Oliver Tuthill Jr.‚Äã

This is an Important Faith-based Movie That Tells the Story of Roman Emperor¬†Constantine the Great, Who United the Roman Empire in 324 A.‚ÄãD.‚Äã During the Great Civil War and Granted Religious Freedom to All.‚Äã

A Global Film for Both the Domestic and International Marketplace.‚Äã

Constantine is a Unique, Singular Film.‚Äã Christian Audiences Throughout the World Will Be Drawn to Its Powerful Message and Historical Impact on Christianity Today.‚Äã

Many of the Themes, Such as Religious Persecution, Are as Prevalent Today as They Were When Constantine Lived, and This Will Resonate With Christians.‚Äã

Pastors and Priests Throughout the World Will Want Their Congregations to See This Film.‚Äã

Evangelists Will Use This Film to Teach and Bring More Followers Into the Church.‚Äã¬†Named Talent Has Signed LOI‚Äôs.‚Äã¬†¬†Four (4) Major Distributors Have Expressed Interest and Based on Budgetary Information Provided to the State of Illinois Department of Commerce and Economic Opportunity the Films Production Accreditation Would Realize an Illinois Tax Credit Over $800,000 and a Certificate Has Already Been Issued.‚Äã.‚Äã

We are seeking an investor who will also get credit as an ‚ÄúExecutive Producer‚Äù.‚Äã¬†¬†

¬†‚ÄúDirector: Oliver W.‚Äã Tuthill Jr.‚Äã has been directing films since he was a child, and by the time he was 14 years old had made over one hundred westerns, dramas and horror movies.‚Äã

He moved to Hollywood in the 1970s and worked as a Day Player for many of the major studios such as Universal, MGM and Columbia.‚Äã

He is a graduate of the Hollywood Film Institute and formed his first production company in 1995 where he made educational films for 10 years, many which are distributed throughout the world.‚Äã

In 2002 he won the Governor‚Äôs Award in Media from then Governor Gary Locke, and in 2003 he won the Horace Mann Award for contributions to education concerning emotional child abuse.‚Äã

In 2004 he formed Blue Wood Films LLC and has produced both documentaries and feature length films.‚Äã

His films have been distributed by Netflix, Passion River Films, Amazon, Entertainment 7, Reality Films, Autumn Tree Productions and Blue Wood Films LLC.‚Äã

He wrote, produced and directed Willatuk: The Legend of Seattle‚Äôs Sea Serpent narrated by Academy Award nominated actor Graham Greene (Dances With Wolves), Wounded Heart: Pine Ridge and the Sioux narrated by Lakota actor Russell Means (Last of the Mohicans), The Right to Bear Armsstarring John Savage (The Deer Hunter)and Questions for Crazy Horsefeaturing Jay Red Hawk (Skins)and Russell Means (Natural Born Killers).‚ÄãIn 2013 he released his newest documentary, the critically acclaimed The Girl Who Loved Animals: Kitty Jones and the Fight for Animal Rights.‚Äã

Tuthill is an experienced film producer, director, editor, composer, director of photography, sound designer and writer.‚Äã

He taught at the Seattle Film Institute for five years, the largest film school in the Northwest.‚Äã

¬†In 2009, Tuthill served as a Nominating Committee Member - Theatrical Motion Pictures, for the 15thannual Screen Actors Awards.‚Äã

¬†Tuthill, a Grammy Award contender in 2011, also composes the soundtracks for most of his films.‚Äã He is an award-winning songwriter and composer and is the founder and President of Blue Pony Trail Music.‚Äã His featured artist is Grammy Award contender and Native American Music Award winner Shadowyze.‚Äã

Their newest release is Say No to the R Word which features spoken words by Russell Means.‚Äã

¬†In 2011 Tuthill was nominated for best musical soundtrack by the Native American Music Awards for his documentary on the life of Lakota warrior Crazy Horse titled Questions for Crazy Horse: Hypothetical Questions for the Strange Warrior of the Lakota Oglala.‚Äã¬†

Tuthill‚Äôs song performed by Shadowyze titled, What Would Crazy Horse Say, was nominated in 2011 by the Native American Music Awards for best historical song.‚Äã

¬†Amateur boxer for 13 years and official correspondent for Ring Magazine for 25 years.‚Äã

Recorded with blues legend John Mayall.‚Äã

Recorded "Night of the Wolf" with rock group Steppenwolf.‚Äã

Opening act for Styx for two years.‚Äã

¬†Worked in Hollywood as a studio musician and songwriter.‚Äã

¬†Taught Blocking and Staging for Camera at the Seattle Film Institute for five years, and was a prior drama instructor in the Theater Department at Seattle Central.‚Äã

Also taught Blocking and Staging for Camera at 911 Media Arts Center in Seattle.‚Äã

Taught Directing Actors for the Camera at the Seattle Central College Film School.‚Äã

¬†Received the Horace Mann Award in 2003 by Antioch University Seattle for his educational films which are distributed worldwide.‚Äã

¬†Worked as a professional actor in Hollywood for over a decade and is a member of SAG-AFTRA.‚Äã

¬†Encouraged by Gunsmoke TV star James Arness to become a film director.‚Äã¬†

¬†Hollywood agencies that represented him include the Willam Felber Agency, Beverly Hecht Agency and the William Kerwin Agency.‚Äã

¬†In the controversial film Brothers in 1977 with Bernie Casey he played a police officer in some shoot out scenes, and was on the poster on the theater board in Hollywood.‚Äã

Worked as a stand in and extra on over 50 films before getting his first speaking part in the TV film Panic In Echo Park.‚Äã

He Broke into Hollywood films by registering with the Hollywood unemployment office as an extra and got his first start as an extra in the 1976 feature film Logan's Run which featured Michael York, Richard Jordan and Farrah Fawcett-Majors, and worked for about a week at MGM Studios in Culver City when they filmed the arena scenes and sat next to Richard Jordan's wife during his scenes.‚Äã

marketingDescription:
Location Summary
The subject property is located in a high barrier to entry market in Salt Lake City, UT.‚Äã The property has great exposure to high traffic counts as it sits between State Street (28,000 AADT) and Main Street (7,500 AADT).‚Äã The property has good ingress and egress with direct access from both streets.‚Äã It also has great access to major freeways including I-15 which is the Major North South Interstate with traffic counts of 209,000 AADT and I-80 which is the major East West Interstate with traffic counts of 118,000 AADT.‚Äã The site is flat and has plenty of parking for most business uses.‚Äã
Salt Lake City Economy
Salt Lake City's expanding economy has boosted its retail fundamentals.‚Äã New construction has been limited in the past five years while demand remains constant, resulting in all-time low vacancies which are now at 2.7%.‚Äã Total employment has grown by 29.1% in the past 10 years while the median household income has increased by 45.8%.‚Äã The strong consumer base is also supported by the fast-growing Lehi and Provo areas, located just south of the Salt Lake City metro area.‚Äã
Retail rents in the Salt Lake City market were rising at a 6.3% annual rate during the second quarter of 2023, and have posted an average annual gain of 6.4% over the past three years.‚Äã In addition to 600,000 SF that has delivered over the past three years (a cumulative inventory expansion of 1.0%), there is 250,000 SF currently underway.‚Äã
Employment in the metro was recently increasing at an annual rate of 3.3%, or a gain of about 26,000 jobs.‚Äã
Buy the R&F Mart Business or Re-tenant the Space
If a new owner choses to buy the R&F Mart Business they will get the opportunity to continue to expand Salt Lake Cities largest Asian Supermarket wholesale and retail grocery store.‚Äã R&F Mart is thriving with a growing client base and 2022 revenue of just under $25,000,000.‚Äã The owner is asking $6,000,000 for the business.‚Äã If a new owner choses to buy the property and re-tenant the R&F mart space of 44,500 SF at a conservative market rent of $18/SF NNN.‚Äã This would allow a new owner to charge $801,000 annually or more for this space.‚Äã
Value Add Thru Rental Increases and Expense Recapture
Salt Lake City experienced healthy economic and population growth over the past decade, along with increasing median income, driving retail consumption.‚Äã Compressed vacancies have given landlords pricing power and rent gains here are among the best in the nation.‚Äã Annual rent growth is currently posting gains of around 6.3%.‚Äã Average asking rents in the metro are approximately $23.00/SF.‚Äã This opportunity gives a new owner the ability to significantly increase the value of this asset by increasing rents over time.‚Äã All tenants pay below market rents and many of the tenants pay rent that is significantly below market rents.‚Äã Additionally, many leases could be changed to a full NNN structure to recapture additional expenses.‚Äã
Property in Great Condition - Pride of Ownership
The current ownership has made many property upgrades and improvements.‚Äã The R&F Mart Building was built in 2020 with the owner spending over $5,900,000 including adding over $650,000 in Coolers and Freezers.‚Äã China Town Plaza has also seen many upgrades since 2019 including over $740,000 in upgrades.‚Äã
Coldwell Banker Commercial is pleased to present the opportunity to purchase an absolute gem of a property including China Town Plaza, Arby's and R&F Mart.‚Äã With the purchase of this investment a new owner will have the choice of either purchasing the entire property with the R&F Mart business or purchasing the property and retenanting the R&F Mart building.‚Äã Any new owner will have immediate cash flow with existing in place tenants including Arby's and the tenants in China Town Plaza while they re-tenant the R&F Mart space or takeover the R&F Mart Business.‚Äã Financials, Rent Roll and Due Diligence materials are available upon execution of a signed Confidentiality Agreement.‚Äã Please do not disrupt the current tenants or tour the property without a scheduled tour.‚Äã Call Paul Pursell at 984-284-9045 for more details or to schedule a tour of the property.‚Äã

description: Core-Plus Retail Asset | The Woodlands, Texas
marketingDescription:
DuWest Realty Investment Services is pleased to present the opportunity to acquire College Park Plaza ("The Property"), a 70,277 square foot (9.914 acres) multi-tenant shopping center in The Woodlands, Texas.‚Äã The Woodlands is a Texas success story in master-planned communities.‚Äã It is an award-winning economic and prosperous growth suburb of Houston (ranked #3 among U.‚ÄãS.‚Äã Metro areas in Fortune 500 headquarters), with over 115,000 residents and is located about 27 miles north of downtown Houston.‚Äã

The Property is ideally located along College Park Drive with immediate access to I-45, which sees a combined 225,684 VPD offering unrivaled access and exposure.‚Äã There are several unique drivers in the immediate submarket including 3 hospitals, an 18,000 member church, a 15,000 student community college and a 3,000 student high school, all within one-half mile of the Property.‚Äã This creates excellent daytime and night-time traffic for the businesses at The Property.‚Äã With the property situated at a highly prominent location within The Woodlands, the investment is set to benefit substantially as this top-rated community continues to densify and grow.‚Äã

The shopping center is leased to a strong line of tenants featuring both national and local credit with an average historical occupancy of 10 years.‚Äã With 89% of the center currently leased, it provides investors a core-plus opportunity with 7,600 square feet available for lease up and the ability to mark to market rents.‚Äã The average rent at the center is ~$26, which is 20-35% under market compared to similar properties in the trade area.‚Äã Moreover, 18 of the 23 in-place tenants lack renewal options and 22% of the rent roll expires in year 1.‚Äã This allows a buyer to immediately push revenue and further capitalize on the upside in the next 2-5 years.‚Äã

The Property also features +/- 38,000 square feet of contiguous "green space" in front of the shopping center.‚Äã Currently unimproved, a buyer can activate this area with an experience-driven dog park, playground, pickle ball courts, or a grab-and-go bar.‚Äã With the addition of weekend food trucks, this under-utilized area would become a first-class amenity, and bring immediate energy to the center and its family-oriented tenants.‚Äã It could also provide a catalyst for lease-up of the remaining vacancy and in-line rent growth.‚Äã Additional rental revenue from the green space has not been modeled herein, however, with a qualified operator, there is yet another opportunity for cash flow upside.‚Äã

College Park Plaza offers the investor a unique opportunity in a Core-Plus Asset in an A+ Houston, Texas submarket.‚Äã The high barriers to entry, lack of options remaining, ability to mark to market rents and activation of the green space provides a high floor, high ceiling investment opportunity in a best-in-class submarket.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
• ‚Äã

    88% of In-Place Tenants have ZERO options remaining (18 of 23) and nearly all of these are under market rate.

  • ‚Äã

    Opportunity to revitalize and amenitize 38,000 SF greenspace as amenity.

  • ‚Äã

    Located amongst behemoth large box retailers such as Walmart Supercenter, HEB, Lowe's, Costco, Sam's Club, Private Schools (19,418 students) and Large Hospital Systems (608 beds).

  • ‚Äã

    Since January 2021, College Park Plaza has only lost 2 tenants, and in that time has signed 3 new leases, 8 renewals (plus 2 out for signature) and 2 expansions.

  • ‚Äã

    The Woodlands offers 35 million square feet of office, retail, hospitality, research, institutional and industrial space with almost 2,200 employers and over 67,000 employees. The Woodlands ranked as the #1 ‚ÄúBest City to Live‚Äù and #1 ‚ÄúBest City to Raise a Family‚Äù in 2023.

  • ‚Äã

    Excellent Accessibility via three points of ingress and egress including from St. Luke's Hospital and two from College Park Drive.

marketingDescription: The Chaney Investment Team with Colliers is pleased to present the Exclusive Listing of Jamestown Village Plaza.‚Äã The 127,440 sf opportunity in Warren, OH has recent updates, and offers are being responded to on a rolling basis.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
Recent Giant Eagle Extension:

Giant Eagle recently signed a 7-year extension, 2 years longer than their option, that includes a rent increase after year 5.

Top Performing Grocery Store:

Giant Eagle is reporting a very strong sales-to-rent ratio of 1.76%, demonstrating the location is very profitable and a long-term site for the company. The tenant invested in a GetGo location next to the property to show further commitment. Ranked #2 best grocery store in the market (Source: PlacerAI: Site Visits)

Strong Trade Area:

With a retail vacancy rate of only 2.7% based on the retail trade area of 582,000 sq ft, the property is the primary location for new business locations and relocations within the market (source: CoStar)

Mismanaged Value Add Ability:

The property has been managed and leased from nearly 3,000 miles away with little to no boots on the ground. As a result, the property offers significant upside potential through the lease-up of vacant space at market rents. With a 33% vacancy rate overall and a 21.5% acancy in the Giant Eagle building, a buyer could add $318,000 in base rent by leasing the vacancy at just $7.63psf net.

Loan Assumption:

The investment is offered subject to a loan assumption with a below market 4.2% interest rate and the existing lender has previously ndicated that it may be open to increasing the leverage through a second mortgage to market LTV.

Recent Capital Expenditures:

Significant near-term capital expenditure with the recent completion of a new roof over Giant Eagle and a fully paved parking lot. The remaining roof on the main building is approximately 10 years old.

Pizza Hut Drive-Through:

Pizza Hut occupies an end-cap suite with a drive-through which offers very low risk with potential upside through re-leasing the space at a higher rent, should they ever vacate.

Amazon Resistant Retailers:

90% of the occupied GLA consists of internet-resistant tenants with grocery, food, and service-oriented uses.

Low Price PSF:

The property will be offered at a small fraction of the replacement cost which offers a low basis and isolates it from the risk exposure of new retail development.

Dollar General operates over 19,100 locations throughout the country. Dollar General‚Äôs net sales increased 10.6% to $37.8 Billion in fiscal year 2022 compared to $34.2 Billion in net sales in fiscal year 2021. description: Monroe County Acreage For Sale with Investment Opportunities
marketingDescription:
If you‚Äôre looking for the convenience of country living on a paved road only minutes from town with plenty of opportunities, this might be the one for you! You won‚Äôt believe the amount of space and prospective uses the home and buildings will present! Sitting on 9.1 surveyed acres this little acreage is packed with something for everyone to enjoy!

¬†

WELCOME TO THE CABIN

The cozy little cabin was built in 2016 and highlights open concept living with many windows bringing in natural light to show a mix of vinyl and concrete flooring, 2 bedrooms (1 non-conforming), and a full bathroom spread out over 1,230 square feet.‚Äã A bonus to this home is a cute, welcoming front porch providing access to a functional 150 square foot attached mud room with a newer hot water heater and laundry area.‚Äã

¬†

TOUR THE INCREDIBLE MULTI-USE BUILDING

A massive 9,000 + square foot steel building was constructed in 2012 and is exploding with opportunities.‚Äã Formerly known as the Dutch Valley Market, it is currently zoned as Rural/Residential but with a special use permit from the County, could be converted back to retail/commercial use.‚Äã The front of the building has an extensive, paved parking lot supporting use for retail/commercial space, has several doors for entrances and exits, and an attractive overhang where you could display products, provide outdoor seating, or simply relax!

¬†

The structure currently boasts a mix of open space, 2nd and 3rd living areas, workshop possibilities, fantastic storage opportunities, and whatever else you can dream of!

¬†

The main open area was previously used for retail business and is presently used for additional living room.‚Äã The current owners constructed a non-load bearing wall to create another living area with another great kitchen/dining space, pantry, ¬Ω bathroom, storage closets, and 2 non-conforming bedrooms.‚Äã

¬†

The North side of the building is separated by a wall and has been used for storage.‚Äã You‚Äôll find an electrical panel in this room too; the electricity is currently disconnected so if desired to be used again, it would need to be re-connected.‚Äã

¬†

The South side of the building has another large kitchen and workspace with a center island, storage closets off the main area and a newer hot water heater.‚Äã A set of stairs leads up to a second story housing a 3rd living room with numerous windows transporting tons of natural light to emphasize a great living/kitchen/dining area, pantry, 2 large bedrooms and a full bathroom.‚Äã

¬†

EXPLORE THE FANTASTIC BUILDINGS & OUTDOOR SPACE

The 40‚Äôx60‚Äô Steel Building has been shown great care and presents multiple uses for a workshop, livestock, parking, 4-H projects, storage, and more! Featuring tall ceilings, a concrete floor, overhead and sliding doors, hydrant, and office, this building has something for everyone.‚Äã

¬†

An older barn sits behind the steel building and presents further opportunities to house livestock and even has a hydrant.‚Äã Sitting behind all of the beautiful buildings is a mix of agricultural space with wire fencing, lots, pasture, some trees, and a pond used primarily to water livestock.‚Äã

¬†

This property also boasts pleasing curb appeal, fantastic yard space with lots of room to play, a great garden space, and room to do whatever you please!

¬†

¬†

¬†

Don‚Äôt overlook the fantastic location! Nestled in an area of Southern Iowa known for extraordinary hunting, recreational, fishing, boating, and camping activities on a paved road near highway 5 between Albia and Moravia, this truly is a rare opportunity to own a unique acreage! Are you ready to schedule your tour?

marketingDescription:
Besen Partners, as exclusive agent for Ownership, is pleased to offer for sale, the retail component of the mixed-use Wyndham Garden LaGuardia South property, located at 92-77 Queens Blvd Rego Park, NY 11374 in the Rego Park neighborhood of Queens, New York.‚Äã

This marketing package presents an opportunity to acquire the retail component of the mixed-use Wyndham Garden LaGuardia South property, located in the Rego Park area of Queens, New York.‚Äã The retail component includes Retro Fitness, Starbucks, and the parking garage, and is being offered for sale as a separate retail condo with an asking price of $20 million.‚Äã

The property is situated on a highly visible corner lot with excellent frontage on Queens Boulevard, a major thoroughfare in the area.‚Äã The retail component comprises a total of 42,532¬± rentable square feet, with Retro Fitness occupying 20,524¬± square feet, Starbucks occupying 2,461¬± square feet, and the parking garage providing 18,374¬± square feet of space.‚Äã

The property benefits from a strong tenant roster, with Retro Fitness and Starbucks both having long-term leases in place.‚Äã Retro Fitness, a popular health club chain, has a triple-net lease with an initial term of 10 years and two 5-year renewal options.‚Äã Starbucks, which includes a drive-thru lane, occupies a prime ground-level space and has a lease in place with favorable terms.‚Äã

The net operating income (NOI) for the retail component of the property is $1,122,960.15, and the cap rate is 5.61%.‚Äã The property is well-positioned to benefit from the strong demand for retail space in the Rego Park area, which has seen significant growth in recent years.‚Äã The area is home to a diverse mix of retail, dining, and entertainment options, and is easily accessible by public transportation and major highways.‚Äã

Overall, this offering presents a rare opportunity to acquire a high-quality retail asset in a prime location with strong tenant demand and favorable lease terms.‚Äã The asking price of $20 million represents a compelling value proposition for investors seeking to capitalize on the growth potential of the Rego Park area.‚Äã

description: Top Rated Stores In Indiana (Placer.ai) | New 10-Year Lease For Urban Air | Major Retail Corridor
marketingDescription:
Discover a retail gem in Merrillville/Hobart, Indiana, boasting top-rated stores and a fully occupied three-tenant center, featuring well-known national tenants.‚Äã Urban Air has recently signed a new lease and is set to open for business in August 2023, adding to the center's allure.‚Äã With a decade remaining on the lease term, Big Lots has been a prominent fixture since 2009, ranked 11 out of 44 most visited Big Lots stores in Indiana, and has over five years left on its lease.‚Äã Xfinity, the third most-visited store in Indiana among 18 stores, has been successfully operating here since 2014.‚Äã

Strategically located at the epicenter of Merrillville's major retail corridor, this center serves as a strong economic driver for the area.‚Äã It is just 0.6 miles away from Southlake Mall, a super-regional mall that attracted 6.02 million visits in the last 12 months, anchored by popular brands such as Kohl's, JCPenney, Macy's, H&M, and Forever 21.‚Äã The area also boasts other major tenants like AMC Theatres, Cooper's Hawk Winery, Express, and Victoria's Secret.‚Äã Moreover, within two miles, notable tenants like Sam's Club, Walmart, Target, Home Depot, Dick's Sporting Goods, Hobby Lobby, Best Buy, Ulta, DSW, T.‚ÄãJ.‚Äã Maxx, Harbor Freight Tools, PetSmart, Nothing Bundt Cakes, McDonald's, BJ's Brewhouse, and many others contribute to the area's vibrant retail landscape.‚Äã

Convenience and accessibility are key strengths of this location, situated just 1.4 miles from the Interstate 65 interchange, with an impressive daily traffic count of 102,870 vehicles.‚Äã Positioned on the signalized, hard-corner intersection of East Lincoln Highway and Colorado Street, the center offers easy ingress and egress from both streets.‚Äã With 645 feet of unobstructed frontage along Lincoln Highway, it captures the attention of approximately 36,228 vehicles each day.‚Äã

Beyond its retail appeal, this location offers a variety of popular attractions within close proximity.‚Äã It is only 12.5 miles away from the illustrious Hard Rock Casino Northern Indiana, a $300 million establishment boasting 200 hotel rooms and attracting 2.2 million annual visitors.‚Äã Additionally, the stunning Indiana Dunes National Park, with 3.18 million annual visitors, is just 15 miles away.‚Äã The Gary/Chicago International Airport (GYY), situated 16 miles away, serves as a full-service airport for corporate, commercial, and cargo users, with an impressive 52 flights per day.‚Äã

The center's success is further supported by its location in a highly populated area with a substantial workforce.‚Äã Approximately 83,089 people reside within five miles, while 31,007 people work within three miles, ensuring a steady flow of potential customers for the thriving retail establishments.‚Äã

TOP NATIONAL BRAND RETAILERS¬†The Investment possesses four top-tier national brand tenants including Wingstop, UBREAKIFIX, Sport‚Äôs Clips, and Jersey Mike‚Äôs, all of which are leaders in their respective businesses.‚Äã Wingstop (NASDAQ: WING) has grown into an international company with more than 1,700 locations and a market cap of $5.74 billion.‚Äã UBREAKIFIX was acquired by Asurion in 2019.‚Äã Asurion and its franchisees employ over 23,000 and possess 700+ locations.‚Äã Jersey Mike‚Äôs, a fast casual sandwich shop through its franchisee network has grown to over 2,400 locations nationwide.‚Äã Sport‚Äôs Clips is a leader in the hair salon industry and boasts revenues exceeding $1.6 billion and has 1,850 locations nationwide.‚Äã

55K VPD + 47% POPULATION GROWTH + LOW RE TAXES¬†The Property benefits from exceptional traffic count of 55,000+ vehicles per day with tremendous corner visibility on the hard lighted intersection of US Highway 12 and Illinois Route 120.‚Äã Since the year 2000, the population within a 5-mile radius has grown by 47%.‚Äã The average household income and population within a 10-mile radius are $116,000 and 365,500 respectively.‚Äã Located in McHenry County, the Property also benefits from significantly lower real estate taxes compared to those of neighboring Cook County.‚Äã

E-COMMERCE RESISTANT TENANTS + NET LEASES¬†The tenant mix at the Property is comprised entirely of service and food-oriented users, providing protection from online retail growth.‚Äã Each tenant at the Property has enhanced their online experience to add value to their brick-and-mortar stores and strengthen their market share.‚Äã The Property‚Äôs four tenants operate under net lease structures and are responsible for their proportionate share of the Property‚Äôs real estate taxes and operating expenses.‚Äã The ‚Äònet‚Äô lease structure safeguards the landlord against future expense growth.‚Äã

OUTLOT TO TOP-TIER WOODMAN‚ÄôS GROCER¬†The Property is positioned on an outlot to Woodman‚Äôs Market, a regionally dominant 24/7, super-grocer with 19 locations across Illinois and Wisconsin.‚Äã Woodman‚Äôs locations operate on a modified warehouse model, which allows them to offer customers low prices and bulk purchases.‚Äã With total company revenue exceeding $2 billion, the average Woodman‚Äôs store is 200,000-400,000 square feet.‚Äã The Lakemoor Woodman‚Äôs location is a top tier performer and the Property shares several ingress/egress points with Woodman‚Äôs.‚Äã

BRAND NEW CLASS-A CONSTRUCTION¬†The Property is a BRAND NEW, Class-A, ground-up multi-tenant building, consisting of 5,200 square feet occupied by Jersey Mike‚Äôs, Sports Clips, UBREAKIFIX, and Wingstop.‚Äã The Property is resting in the greater Lakemoor Commons development, a multi-building outlot development comprised of the Property, a single-tenant Starbucks, a single-tenant Chipotle, a single-tenant Buona Beef, a single-tenant Heartland Dental, a single-tenant Taco Bell, three fuel stations, one additional multi-tenant retail center and a future Advocate Aurora Health Center‚Äì all benefitting from tremendous cross traffic.‚Äã

marketingDescription: Disney Investment Group, on behalf of the ownership, has been exclusively retained to offer an investor the opportunity to acquire Valley Ranch Centre (the ‚ÄúProperty‚Äù), a 111,211 square foot neighborhood shopping center located in Coppell, Texas, a very affluent and growing suburb in the dynamic Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex.‚Äã Recently renovated in 2022, Valley Ranch Centre is 93.3% leased and has experienced significant leasing velocity during the past year.‚Äã The Property is anchored by Club 4 Fitness (50,000 square foot corporate-backed lease with multiple, high-net worth personal guarantors) along with Dollar Tree and a new AutoZone store.‚Äã Club 4 Fitness is a rapidly growing fitness chain with 35 locations nationwide including five (5) locations in the Dallas/Ft.‚Äã Worth market.‚Äã Valley Ranch Centre is surrounded by tremendous average household incomes exceeding $148,830 with a dense and growing population of more than 78,059 residents within a 3-mile radius.‚Äã This offering represents a unique opportunity for an investor to purchase a very well-located and well-established neighborhood shopping center in the one of the four (4) largest MSA‚Äôs in the United States.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
Well-Located, Anchored Neighborhood Center in Booming Dallas/Ft. Worth.

Valley Ranch Centre is a premier 111,211 square foot neighborhood shopping center strategically located at the signalized intersection of MacArthur Blvd. and Beltline Rd. in Coppell, Texas. Built in 1989 and renovated in 2022, Valley Ranch Centre is currently 93.3% leased and anchored by Club 4 Fitness, Dollar Tree and a new AutoZone store. Club 4 Fitness signed a 10-year corporate lease with multiple high-net worth personal guarantors backing its lease and is experiencing extremely strong Membership growth since opening its facility in 2021 (Club 4 Fitness‚Äô 2022 annual sales increased 130% over the prior year). Valley Ranch Centre is proximal to the Dallas Area Rapid Transit (DART) Rail Line and located approximately 1.5 miles from Cypress Waters, a massive 1,000-acre, $3.5 billion master planned/mixed-use community under development that is expected to feature 6.5 million square feet of office space and 10,000 residential units upon completion. Numerous major employers including Nokia, 7-Eleven, CoreLogic, Signet Jewelers, Brinker International, Morgan Stanley and many other companies have an existing corporate presence within Cypress Waters.

Very Strong Leasing Momentum Continues.

In less than 15 months, the current ownership has taken Valley Ranch Centre from 74.7% leased to 93.3% leased including a new 10-year lease with AutoZone and the center benefits from Club 4 Fitness‚Äô strong customer draw to the property. Prior to Club 4 Fitness‚Äô current tenancy, a Tom Thumb grocery store successfully operated at this location for approximately 30 years and helped establish Valley Ranch Centre as a preferred neighborhood shopping center serving Coppell and Las Colinas. Having experienced a significant increase in occupancy rate and net operating income, Valley Ranch Centre can still be acquired at a significant discount to replacement cost.

Cash Flow Stability with Strong Rental Growth & Below-Market Rents.

Club 4 Fitness, AutoZone and Dollar Tree provide cash flow security while many of existing shop tenants have been at Valley Ranch Centre for well over 10 years. The average annual base rent for tenants at Valley Ranch Centre is $15.09 per square foot which is considered well-below market. Market rents in the immediate submarket average between $24-$32 per square foot depending on space size and configuration. Over a 10-year hold period, the compound annual growth rate (CAGR) is 2.1 % for Valley Ranch Centre. Less than one-third of the shopping center‚Äôs gross leasable area (GLA) associated with tenant leases will expire prior to December 2029, thus providing cash flow stability with continued rent growth. Approximately 74% of the existing tenants either do not have renewal options or have at-market renewal options.

Exceptional Demographic Profile with Strong Daytime Population.

Average household incomes surrounding Valley Ranch Centre are $141,891 and $148,830 within a 1-mile radius and 3-mile radius, respectively. The population in 2022 includes 18,283 residents and 78,059 residents within the same radii, respectively. Within a 5-mile radius, the population includes 235,920 residents with average household income of $123,163. The projected annual population growth rate from 2021-2026 exceeds 2.5% within a 1-mile radius. Traffic counts at the intersection of Beltline Rd. and MacArthur Blvd. total more than 50,699 vehicles per day.

Unencumbered Asset.

Valley Ranch Centre is being offered free and clear of any existing debt.

New Roof Installed with Long Term Roof Warranty.

The shopping center‚Äôs entire roofing system was replaced in 2018 with a single-ply thermoplastic polyolefin (TPO) membrane and includes a full roof warranty until 2039.

description: Opportunity to acquire 3.47 acres, site plan approved for 44,090 gross SF for restaurant and retail
marketingDescription:
Colliers, on behalf of the City of Tamarac, is pleased to present this unique opportunity to acquire and develop the third and final phase of the Tamarac Village project which consists of 3.47 acres of commercial property (site plan commercial parcels, C-1 and C-2) currently site plan approved for 44,090 gross square feet for restaurant and retail development.‚Äã

The city-owned Site is located on Commercial Boulevard at NW 91st Avenue in Tamarac, Florida and is adjacent to the newly constructed Tamarac Village apartments and a brand new Tamarac Village public park.‚Äã Tamarac Village is a 25-acre mixed-use project, located in the heart of Broward County.‚Äã The first development phases are now complete with a newly constructed 21-acre gated apartment complex with 401 luxury residential units and clubhouse; as well as a newly constructed .75-acre public park with public art installations, a large splash pad, and a new amphitheatre that will be programmed by the City for community events and is directly adjacent to the commercial parcels.‚Äã

The final 3.47-acre Tamarac Village-Commercial phase for restaurant and retail development is currently site plan approved for 44,090 gross square feet of commercial restaurant/retail development with outdoor dining and 255 parking spaces.‚Äã The City‚Äôs vision for the commercial development includes at least one sit-down full-service nationally recognized chain restaurant/upscale food hall and/or brew pub, along with a blend of complimentary food/beverage uses which can include an ice cream shop, coffee shop and/or bakery, etc.‚Äã Structured parking would be a welcomed addition to the project.‚Äã The City is amenable to working with the selected developer on proposed site plan changes.‚Äã Further, the City is pleased to offer a significant development benefit with already approved entitlements for the off-site stormwater/drainage requirement for the developer to construct.‚Äã

Bids Due November 16, 2023 at 3pm EST

All Questions and Submissions for this Request for Proposals, RFP 23-37R, should be submitted through the City‚Äôs website:

https://tamarac.‚Äãorg/bids

    Tamarac Village in close proximity to the Tamarac Commerce Park that has attracted several new major employers including Amazon (600 employees); Sonny‚Äôs CarWash Factory HQs expansion (600 employees); William R. Nash Contractors HQs (400 employees) and more.

Marcus & Millichap is pleased to present 12113 Garland Road, a 20,750-square-foot automotive retail and service center situated on 3.72-acres, with prime frontage and exposure located at 12113 Garland Road, Dallas, Texas.‚Äã The subject property is split between two parcels, an approximately 1.89-acre tract zoned Regional Retail (RR) and an approximately 2.01-acre tract zoned Multiple Commercial (MC-3).‚Äã The asset currently features 20,750 square feet of improvements, with staggered lease turnover, providing the opportunity for stabilized income on a covered land-play.‚Äã The subject property is located proximate to national credit retailers and is proximate to major thoroughfares, including Northwest Highway and Interstate 635.‚Äã

The city of Dallas, Texas is widely-known as the top commercial real estate investment market in the United States, and East Dallas specifically is currently viewed by many investors as the next big-boom submarket in Dallas-Fort Worth.‚Äã The subject property is located on Garland Road, which connects to Gaston Avenue, a main artery that connects downtown Dallas to Old East Dallas, Lower Greenville, Deep Ellum, and Lakewood.‚Äã For this reason, the high traffic volume has created a boom in new developments in this immediate area.‚Äã Developers are aggressively targeting this market with an influx of multifamily and retail developments to support the growing population and demand.‚Äã With lower rents and overall development costs than Uptown, and the accessibility to Downtown and major freeways, what was once an outskirt of the city is now main-and-main.‚Äã The ease and access to recent transportation technology has cut down commuting time and costs, giving residents more freedom and options.‚Äã

Overall, 12113 Garland Road provides a new investor or speculative developer the incredible opportunity to acquire a large-scale land tract in one of Dallas-Fort Worth's most rapidly transitioning submarkets.‚Äã The favorable zoning of RR and MC-3, allow for a multitude of new retail and mixed-use redevelopment opportunities once all existing leases have expired.‚Äã In addition, the close proximity to major thoroughfares, such as Northwest Highway and Interstate 635, provide the opportunity to capture high trafÔ¨Åc counts towards major trade areas.‚Äã

marketingDescription:
Marketplace at Seminole Towne Center | Largest & Most Dominant Open-Air Center in North Orlando | $5.4M NOI | 3.4% CAGR

Colliers, as exclusive broker, is pleased to present the opportunity to acquire Marketplace at Seminole Towne Center (the ‚ÄúProperty‚Äù), the largest, most dominant open-air shopping center north of downtown Orlando, serving the high-income and booming submarkets of Sanford and Lake Mary.‚Äã The Property is located prominently at the super-regional interchange connecting Interstate 4 (162,500 VPD) with Orlando‚Äôs ‚Äúperimeter‚Äù beltway formed by SR 417 (41,800 VPD) and SR 429 (27,500 VPD), with the final link under construction to be completed by the end of 2023, a major inflection point fueling the growth in the surrounding areas and vaulting property values.‚Äã
investmentHighlights:
The Largest & Most Dominant Center North of Downtown Orlando

  • ‚Äã

    Nearly 4 million visits annually, ranking the Property in the top 6% of shopping centers in each; Orlando MSA, Florida and Nationally (Placer.ai).

  • ‚Äã

    The Property being sold is 327,000 SF on +/- 41 acres, but when combined with the shadow Super Target with grocery, the Property is the largest open-air center north of downtown Orlando and totals nearly 518,000 SF on +/- 58 acres.

  • ‚Äã

    Regional center of gravity for grocery, off-price shopping, dining, service and wellness between Altamonte Springs (10 miles south) and Orange City (10 miles north).

  • ‚Äã

    Preferred shopping center destination for anchor tenants and traditional ‚ÄúMall‚Äù inline tenants interested in relocating from Seminole Towne Center Mall, as evidenced by recent additions to the Property ‚Äì Burlington, Bath & Body Works, Carter‚Äôs and Claire‚Äôs.

Enhanced Super-Regional Connectivity ‚Äì Completion of SR-429 / SR-417 Beltway

  • ‚Äã

    Similar to most metro areas, Orlando has an outer loop beltway SR-417 / SR-429 that runs a 20-mile circumference around downtown Orlando and connects at Interstate 4 (I-4) which bisects Orlando. ¬†

  • ‚Äã

    The beltway and the interchange with I-4 in Sanford will be completed in late 2023 and will create an even more dominant super-regional node benefiting the Property as shoppers in northwest Orlando will have easy interstate access to the area. ¬†

  • ‚Äã

    The area will also see even more explosive growth from office and residential development due to the super-regional nature created by the confluence of the two most significant roadways in metro Orlando.

Booming Sanford and Lake Mary Submarket

  • ‚Äã

    The Lake Mary / Sanford area is home to the most dominant and highly sought-after Class A suburban office submarket in Orlando, with over 27,000 employees, creating significant daily traffic for the Property. These office parks are occupied by today‚Äôs leading financial services, insurance and technology companies; and as a result, serve as the basis for the nearby high demographic housing.¬†

  • ‚Äã

    The Property is approximately 4 miles west from historic downtown Sanford, which sits on the shore of Lake Monroe and is undergoing a major renaissance. Historic downtown Sanford is the most buzzworthy arts, food and music district north of downtown Orlando evidenced by the many destination restaurants, craft breweries and new planned mixed-use developments.

  • ‚Äã

    1,500 new residential units have been added within 5-miles over the past 5 years, with another 2,700 units planned or currently underway.

  • ‚Äã

    5-Mile Average Household Incomes are $112,000 (Orlando MSA = $96,000) and are projected to grow to $130,000 over the next 5 years.

Ideal Income Stability with NOI Growth Potential

  • ‚Äã

    Strong performing, shadow-anchor Super Target with grocery owns their own parcel and promotes cross-shopping as it welcomes 1.4 million visitors annually (Placer.ai).

  • ‚Äã

    All anchors have a history of renewal at the Property ‚Äì Marshalls (S&P: A), Ross Dress for Less (S&P: BBB+), Big Lots, Petco, Old Navy, World Market; except for Burlington, which was added November 2022 on a new 10-year lease.

  • ‚Äã

    Big Lots reaches terminal expiration in 2032 and is approximately 50% below market.

  • ‚Äã

    Owned outparcels include separately parceled Taco Bell (ground lease), Mr. & Mrs. Crab, as well as 3 multi-tenant outparcel strip buildings with strong performing restaurant tenants such as Chipotle, Panera Bread, Firehouse Subs, and Keke‚Äôs Breakfast Caf√© and leading service tenants such as Massage Envy, Bright Now Dental, Club Champion, T-Mobile, AT&T and Supercuts. Approximately 30% of the Property revenue comes from these single-tenant and strip building outparcels.

  • ‚Äã

    21 of 29 shop tenants hit terminal expiration over the next 10-years, providing maximum flexibility to mark-to-market rents and continue to curate and upgrade the tenant merchandising plan.
